\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid16009454 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Could I have your name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Edith Annie Radford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 2 Beara Cottages, Landscove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And your marital status? You are married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, married. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Can you remember the year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. In, yes, in - - 9 - November 11th 1921.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Can you remember the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. May the fourth 1898.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And your birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Charles, North Devon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Whereabouts is Charles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well, it's between - South Molton and Barnstaple. It's seven miles from South Molton and seven miles from Barnstaple, we'r
e in - that was in the middle. There's just villages you know around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that a farm cottage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no. No, private. Private house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many years did you live in the house where you were born, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you stay there very long do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh no, 'cos I - I came down here when I was six years old. Well say - say I was three when I - when we left Charles 'cos then we went down to Bonham, another little cottage called Walham. That's where my sister was born.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Is that very far away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, that isn't very far away, about ten minutes I expect. In the same parish, in the same parish, it's all in the same parish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You stayed there 'til you were six did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We - we stayed - we stayed there 'til we came down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did you live when you came here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 At Tidwell Cottages. That's by - up near the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Is that in Staveton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, Landscome. Yes, Landscome. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you stay there until 1918 or did you move before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh we - we - we - we stayed there - oh, when we came down here we stayed here. Was in that - were in that cottage - when my - my father died when he was - thirty - thirty - thirty-six and - now I was six years old when I came here
 so how many years would that be now? Because we had to come out when he died you see. I'd be about - thirty-three would it be. Say thirty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Thirty years in that cottage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. That's near enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, sixty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh, when I was born? Oh goodness, no I don't, I don't know how old he was. I never asked mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 About twenty or thirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, I should think it'd be about that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did he come from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Stook Rivers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
That's near Barnstaple too. But it's a different way than what - than what we lived you see. But it's - well 'tis only about three mile from Barnstaple from where Stook Rivers is, o
nly about three miles from Barnstaple. It's not in the same area as - as we are, it's - it's down near - Chilhampton, around there. That way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Farm work - farm labourer I suppose. Because - but he - he mostly did all the 
ploughing - the out - the - field work, he mostly did. Ploughing and - and harvesting and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he have any other jobs at all that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not - not on the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Outside the farm did he have any other work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Only his own work, his gardening and - and getting rid of things like that, he - that was all in - in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever do any other job after he was a farm labourer or did he stay that all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He stayed at that all his life until he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he do any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say you moved from Charles to Wollan and Wollan to Tidwell, why did you make these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - he - h
e wanted a change. He thought he'd try South Devon you see. And - we come down here in March, but I don't know what - what year it - well I was six years old. And I'm seventy - seventy - seventy-four now. So that's when it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 as the farming better in South D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 evon than in North Devon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, yes, it was better - it was better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well because - where we lived was awfully isolated. We were so far you see from Barnstaple, we were so far from - South Molton, it was a job to 
get there. When we came down here it was quite different really. I mean, Staveton - was quite near to catch a train you see and - and Buckfastleigh wasn't very far to walk. We were quite happy when we came down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So it was quite lonely isolation in the other place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, it was, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many brothers or sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Got one brother. And one sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were they older or younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Younger. I'm the eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How much younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well my brother is - seventy-two, and my daughter - my sister is seventy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you all came within two or three years of each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes, that's right, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That' I can't tell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 About twenty or thirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Say twenty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She was about the same age as your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, yes, she must have been about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Wollan. She was born in Wollan.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did she have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 W
ell - home there - home at Wollan and Charles - she did teach - sewing in the school. Was when - when she was home there. But that was all she did home there because - she used to go and teach sewing in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was she a schoolmistress then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no, no, no, only a sewing - teacher, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How old would she be when she started doing this, would that be her first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that was - well I - I expect I was about a week old and that because she used - what - I wasn't - old e
nough to go to school, she used to take me up with her - and so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 This was after she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, after she got married, after she got married, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember if your mother did anything before she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, no. She 
- she stayed home with her mother and father. Because her mother wasn't very strong, and she had to stay home and look after - her. And her father - 'cos her father was a churchwarden there, he used to - well he was Sexton and he looked after the church a
nd rang the bells, help rang the - ring the bells.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that a full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, full time job. Yes. And of course it - you know what belongs to that, always needed there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What does a Sexton do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He looks after the churchyard, he 
looks - he sees to everything you know. The burials and the marriages and - you know, he got to prepare things for it. And the bells and - and all the lighting. He does all that, he used to do all that. He was eighty-nine when he died. An old age wasn't i
t. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your parents move over here when you came over here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes, yes. My grandmother come with us. When we came down me grandmother come with us. And - well we came down in March and she died in May. So that was sad. Not - not being here very long. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your mother ever have any part time - jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No. No. Not - not home there. No. 'Cos she got - when she moved - when we came here, after a little while, after we got settled in, she - she took in washing Laundry. And then - she 
started - after a few years she started doing the school out, cleaning the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Is that the school just up the road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that's the school up the road, yes. And then - when I got married I took on - helped her. Well then when she passed on I
 took it on. So the school was - in our hands for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you were a sort of a caretaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, caretaker and - and a canteen - the canteen came in whiles I was there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When did that come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 About fourteen year ago. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you were in charge of that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, I was in charge of that as well. See the dinner and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So your mother didn't do any work until she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And then she helped in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Which school was it she helped in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 This is the one up here, Landscome school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But when she was teaching the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 sewing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 Oh - C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 harles. Charles. Yes, Charles school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Your mother worked after she had children, who looked after the children while she was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well I - when - when do you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When you were at Charles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh well you see the other two wasn't born then. See not - I don't know, I expect my grandmother looked after 'em I expect. She lived with my mother you see. So I expe
ct she looked after 'em, I can't remember. But I know she used to take me, I wasn't - I wasn't - one or two years old, I was quite a baby like. She took me up to be out of the way I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did she put you while she was working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - well I - I used to run about and do what I was mind to I suppose. I can't remember, but I know she used to take me up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of hours would she work on the school, when she was just doing the sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh - well to - two to four. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Every - yes, every afternoon. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about when she was doing the laundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh that's a full - that was up to her, I mean she used to do it - in her own time that you see 'cos they used to bring it to her you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of people would bring laundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 All different kinds. Oh she had lots of people do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was this the sort of custom in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes, yes, yes yes. Well they had no steam laundries, see, she used to it - do it by hand you see, and 
have those old - those old fashioned - coppers to put it in and all that, there was nothing like - nothing easy work in they days. And - heat the irons by the fire. Oh it was hard work in they days. It was. Well when I got married I used to help her a bit
 then you see, in my spare time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would she do it for the whole neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Not for the whole - well no, it was - like - gentry people, well they called themselves gentry. Lord Helpston used to come and - the Chichton and - such as they people 
used to bring it. Well and - well - some people that lived in Doctor Moles place, something like that, they'd send out their washing you see. And - and mother used to do it. Not poor people. They used to bring it to mother 'cos mother couldn't fetch it yo
u see, and they used to come and fetch it - at the weekend.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How much would she change for the laundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well so much a - article. I can't remember how much, but there's so much a article I know. 'Cos she had books you see to put it all by - write it all down in. But it weren't very much in they days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Which house do you remember most of when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well I - I remember Charles as well a little bit. I can - I can picture the house - now in me mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many rooms did that have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Two bedrooms. And a - and a kitchen downstairs as far as I remember and a - and a little backhouse. It wasn't very big. Little back house. And we - we - all we three children used to sleep in one bed - bedroom. Then 'cos when we lived there we w
ere only babies you see. I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What was the other house like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
I can't remember Wollan so well. I can't remember. I - I know we had a - what they called a parlour there and a kitchen here. But I can't remember the bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What was the back house used for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh they used to keep their - they used to keep their wood in it and - wasn't - wasn't a nice place. Just a - well I suppose - storage place, that's right, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have any reception rooms or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, we - we only had one kitchen, we had to - do everything in the same - kitchen that was - this kitchen and sitting room and all. Home there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did anyone else besides your parents and brother and sister live in the house, did you have any relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Nobody else, nobody else. Only me grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Your grandmother was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, me grandmother lived with us - until we come down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was your grandfather dead then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He died, he died, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You didn't have any lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your mother ever pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She never had anyone living in to help, you say your mother helped with the laundry when she came over here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was the washing done at home or sent out when you were at Charles and Wollan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh they did it home. Oh they did it all at home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It was only when you came here that she started doing other peoples washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your mother or father mend or make the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Mother did. And she used to do it - well she was a busy woman - she used to do it for other people as well, dressmaking. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of people would she do it for, anybody who wanted it doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Anybody who want it done, yes, yes. But she had to give up in the end because it was too much you see. But this - she started this before she took on the school. This dressmaking to help - ends meet you see. But she didn'
t always get what she - what she wanted, she never - some of 'em went off and never paid anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was this gentry again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, it was mostly poor people. Poor people that done that, not gentry. I don't think she'd take on gentry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of clothes would she make?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Just plain dresses and skirts and - well underwear then in they days. She used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did she ever make your father's clothes at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 His shirts. She always made his shirts. - Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did she get the material from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh she - she - from Mr Stall - Stall's in Totnes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was he a shopkeeper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, a shopkeeper, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would she ever buy the family clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Didn't - well the only thing she bought was coats. You - she - she couldn
't make - well she have - she has made coats but - but when you wanted a best coat, she used to buy one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where would you get that from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Totnes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about before you moved to this area, would she make the clothes in Wollan and Charles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
They had - they had to go - yes, they had to go to Barnstaple. To Barnstaple to do their shopping. 'Cos - South Molton was - bit more hilly to go. And they used to - Fridays they went - what they called a market trap goes in, a trap, only a trap - pony t
rap and they used to go in with them. Get what they wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who was looking after the trap then, was it the farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The farmer - a farmer it was. He was called - Oxtable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was he your father's farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, he wasn't father's farmer, no
. No. He - he just farmed a bit away from us. No, father - father used to farm for a man - man called Thorn, just across - well it was down at Wollan, that's where he - that's where he was working. Wollan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were the houses you lived in part of the farm or were they separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh they're separate from the farm. Separate from the farm. Yes. They used to have to pay rent for them. Oh no, not like it is today. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your mother ever buy clothes new or would she ever get second hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, never - she never got second hand, never bought second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 hand. Perhaps sometimes - a person would hand down a coat or anything. But she never bought nothing. If they - they was grown out of it, any children was grown out of it, they ma}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893  hand it down then but - that was all. That wasn't very often. Because they couldn't do it in they days you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about things like jumble sales?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Didn't - never had it, there was - there was nothing like that in those days. Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So on the whole she made the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes she did. She did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your father ever have a go at anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about shoes or boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We used to have to wear hobnail boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Girls as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where would you get them from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Totnes, oh we - yes, we had everything in Totnes in Stalls'. 'Cos they used to deliver you see, 'cos you couldn't keep on running in there in they days. No, they used to deliver, we had everything - in that way - to Stalls'. And 
we dealt with them for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often would you get new boots or shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh - I can't hardly tell you that. Well we used to have to wear them Sundays and Saturdays and all the rest of it, one pair of boots, in they days. And it was hobnails too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that for longer harder wearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes, I suppose they last longer see. 'Cos in those days the boots wasn't like they are today you know. Was all - used to crack stones, and - put them all on the roads, and then they had a roller to roll them
 in. Well - perhaps they stones would be on - on the road for two or three days, well you had to walk on they hard stones, see. You'd cut your feet to pieces.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So it was more an economical thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that's what it was. It was. It was. It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your father ever help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Sometimes. But he - he hadn't got much time - well he'd help with the dishes or - tidy up the fireplace or anything like that, but you see he was - he wasn't home much. 'Co
s he was down to the farm six o'clock in the morning. And he didn't used to come home 'til six o'clock in the evening. So he didn't have much time. And he used to have to go and do his gardening in the moonlight. Because they had to work Saturdays as well
 then you see. They never had no time off at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he do the gardening for a hobby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, for himself. Himself. Yes, in the moon light they used to go out - and do it. My brother used to help when he got old enough. When he got old enough. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things did he grow in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh everything. Everything, vegetables and potatoes, everything you can think of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was it a very big garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, a big garden. Well if you go up past them old cottages you just have a look in and see, you'll see how big it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about the ones in Wollan and Charles, did you have a garden there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, but not so big. Not so big. I can't remember Charles one. But I know Wollan very well. That was a nice - they used to have a nic
e flower garden one side I know, I remember the flowers up against the wall. And the garden was very nice too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you grow flowers and things like that in it as well as vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well, that - that - mother and I used to do the flowers. Or mother used to do them when - hom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
 in Wollan and - and her mother. Used to take an interest in it when - when we were home in - up North Devon. But when we came down here of course I used to help mother then with the flower garden. She was very fond of flower
s. Got any - several prizes in flower show. And so did I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Arranging them and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right, yes, that's right. I've got several first prizes, and so did mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever enter any vegetables?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, yes, he had prizes for vegetables. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he have a prize marrow or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not a marrow but he had potatoes and carrots and - parsnips, and - and savoy, things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What's a savoy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh it's a great big cabbage. Great big cabbage. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Really good soil?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh yes, lovely. 'Course they - they allowed manure then you see from the farm, they was given manure from the farm, that was a privilege. From the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever sell his vegetables elsewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 ever - sell 'em, we couldn't se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 ll 'em, we had too many mouths to feed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So did he keep you in vegetables all year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You didn't have to go out and buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, no, no. No. No. Never bought no vegetables, sometimes if 
- there was a poor potato crop - mother would have to buy a few potatoes, that was all. But otherwise we - we never - we never wanted for anything, always had - stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever have anything like a pig or livestock of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. My father used to keep pigs. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many pigs did he have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well he - soon as one was gone he'd have another one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He had one at a time did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that's right. Sometimes he had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did he keep the pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Over in - he had a pig
s house across - from the cottages. There's a lane, I daresay - I don't know if you did notice it, a lane goes in opposite those houses or a - a yard. I suppose you'd call it. Well he - that's where we used to have to feed the pigs to. And we used to let 
'em - go out and - mother used to go out on the - wood, 'cos we had piles of wood on - on that green then, so we used to go out sit on the wood, mother used to take her sewing out there and do it. What she could do by hand. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have a pig in Wollan and Charles do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, they had pigs down there as well. And a donkey. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What was the donkey used for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well it - my grandfather used to - go to South Molton with him. He had a little - you know, trap thing to put on 
him, then they used to go to South Molton with the donkey and trap you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It was a sort of a riding thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have any chickens or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. We used to keep fowls. Chickens. Ducks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you eat the pig at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes. Yes. Well they always kept a pig, and it was ten or fourteen score. Well they used to kill and the butcher used to come and cut it up, cut the pieces for mother to put in salt and take the other half with hi
m. And that used to pay for the meal that they'd had for the pig. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that common practice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, common practice with everybody. That's what they all used to do. Sometimes they used to keep two. Just depends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you find that the meat and vegetables you had around the actual house kept you in stock for the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes, well - you see, they - in those days there were rabbits too. And - we used to have a rabbit in and that, well we used to - we used to buy that, one of the - Mr Se
arle used to live in this house and - well they was only sixpence each in they day. Sixpence each yes. So we used to have a rabbit to help make up sometimes you see. And the butcher was very good what mother used to deal off. He - and he had bones or scra
ps or anything like that for make a stew, he'd give her that you see on top of her joint. Oh they were very good then, and he'd always give her a bit of suet I suppose they were able to do it in those days. We never starved.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would it be pig and rabbit mainly for the meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh no. Oh no. Oh not mainly, no. We had - we had - well mother used to make up stews with the beef or whatever - chops, or whatever they had you see, and roast. Oh no, it - variation of food there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often a week would you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well we used to have a roast - a roast on Sunday. Then the rest of the week it - mother used to make up different - meals. What she could do, what - you know, what she was able to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time of day would you have the meat meal do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 One o'clock. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would your father come home for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes, we would all do at midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Every day of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Every day of the week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time would breakfast be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well father used t
o have to have his be - about half past five. See, in his work six o'clock then, he - and we - we used to have ours about eight o'clock when we got up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things did you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh father would have only just a bit of bread
 and butter or something like that because he hadn't got - he didn't fancy anything cooked so early as that in the morning. And - then he used to take some bread and cheese and some cake - and ten o'clock they'd have - some cider, they were allowed cider,
 and ate their bread and cheese and - and whatever they had else. They wouldn't come back for breakfast, no, he couldn't. Too far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How far away was the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not very far but where he was working - see, in the fields you see. Of course miles
 and miles he'd be out sometimes. Well you - when you come down over Turners Hill you look up over they hills - in front of you coming down Tambridge Hill, he had to go right up top of there. Yes, and right down Combe. Coo he had some miles to go didn't h
e dad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you' - have breakfast about eight o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When you were at school would you come home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We came home to dinner then. Because there were - there wasn't no - no canteen then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But the school was just round the corner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Just up round the corner by the church there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you'd come back for the midday meal about one o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When would the next meal be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 About six. Or just after six when father comes home
. Well sometimes mother used to fry bacon and egg. And potatoes, she always cooked something in the evening. Either bacon and egg or something like that, or - or different - see variation that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you'd have two cooked meals a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, two cooked meals a day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would you call that third meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well that - that was when - mother used to fry for father when he came home you see, well then we used to have a bit - bacon and potato - because she had her own bacon you 
see. We had bacon nearly every night, fried bacon and potatoes if there wasn't no eggs, or - or a bit of fish if the fish came around you see. Like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The fishmonger came round with a horse and cart did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, journeyed from Paignton. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He came out all this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often a week would he come out then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Come twice a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was this tea or supper, the last meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 This - this - that was the last meal we had. We might have a drink before we 
went to bed but that was all. 'Cos we had to be in bed by seven o'clock, we children. And mother - sometimes we used to have a cup of cocoa or something I think the last thing and father. But we were in bed by seven o'clock we children were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So it was basically three meals a day at roughly the same time every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. That's right, that's right, oh yes, it's regular at meals, regular times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Anything special happen on Sunday, did you have the same mealtimes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, only - oh the same mealtime, we kept to our mealtime. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about Sunday with your father, would he be out in the fields still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no, not Sunday, he didn't work Sunday. Not - no, no. No. No, no, no, he didn't do nothing on Sundays in that way. He was - Superintend}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 nt of the Sunday school and he used to go to Sunday school Sundays you see. He was the local preacher as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever do anything like improvements or repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. He hadn't got the time. No, he hadn't got the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever help with things like dressing or undressing you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh I think he - yes, when - when we were small he used to. Yes, he used to help mother then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever give you a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, he never bathed us, he was afraid of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who did that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Mother. Yes. He may dry us. But he wouldn't have nothing to do with us in the water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever tell you stories or read to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things did he tell you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well that was Bible stories too, my father was a - a good man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Your father didn't help bath you because he was afraid of the water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And he'd read to you and tell you Bible stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, I - h
e used to take - take me to - meetings at Staveton Sunday afternoons. He used to take us, 'cos he was a local preacher as well as - he was - he was a lot in the chapel, and - that was Baptist down there you see, he was really a Baptist. Well he used to ta
k
e us down there every Sunday afternoon. And then we come to our own chapel in the evening. Yes, the Methodist church up here. And - and he - he's taken us - taken us to Buckfastleigh or Ashburton sometimes, he's had to go there, because he used to have to
 go to Ashburton to get his hair cut and he used to take us with him sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What day would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Saturdays. Only Saturday evenings, because he didn't leave work you see 'til six o'clock. All this had to be done after six o'clock Saturday evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would he ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes. Yes, he has done. If mother wanted to go out, well - well she - say she wanted to go to Buckfastleigh or Ashburton, well then - he would let her go of a Saturday evening when - when he was home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But she'd have to do a lot of it after six o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 After he's home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever have any tasks that you had to regularly carry out at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, not really. Not really. J
ust a - just the ordinary - work what we - we were put to do Saturday mornings, that was all, but nothing else. That come - that was a routine you see. But we - we - oh, well I used to have to scrub the stairs down. And - clean the knives and forks, or an
y general thing like that. My daughter used to have to - wash the dishes and help with the dusting. The general housework then, what we - what we could do, that's what we had to do. That's me sister, yes, both of us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would your brother do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He had to cut up the sticks and - and do all outside work like that. Bring in the coal and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you, as the oldest child, help the younger ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, I did. I had to wash my - my sister because she was young, had
 to wash her and - do her hair, we used to have to do the hair up in tresses in those days. And I used to have to do that. And sometimes - I'd have to help feed her, when she was very small. But as she gradually got bigger of course she could feed herself
 then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about the brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He was all right, he fended for himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they help you in any way, with errands or bits and pieces?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not then, he was too young. You see, they couldn't carry groceries or nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you carry on these tasks that you did after you left school on Saturday - morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh yes. Excuse me. No, I - I went out to service as soon as I - soon as I was thirteen. Yes, as soon as I left school, yes. I had to have a certificate to go you see the
n in those days. And because mother was glad of the money. But it weren't very much money they got then. I had half a crown a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you live in at the Doctor's, did you go straight to the Doctor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I didn't go straight to the - I went - 
first I went into Ashburton in a butcher's shop. Mother thought it'd break me in a bit you see in there. Well from there I went up to a place called Moorside, Ashburton. And there I went as house parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 maid. I was there for three years. And - then I - I 
felt that I - I wanted a change then because the mistress wasn't very good up there. She got - she got ever so nasty. And she accused you of doing things what you didn't do you see, and - one day she put some money on - under the - the old lady, she - the
y
 had - he had his mother living with 'em, well I used to have to look after the old lady's part. And she put some money under some - under something to catch me out. And she said, I'll have the policeman for you. Well I - the money was still there, I hadn
'
t took the money. Oh she - she - oh she was dreadful, yes, she was. So I thought to myself well if she's going to start that caper I'm going to leave, I'm not going to stand he for that. So then I went from there to Doctor Mull's. Redmount that's right. I
 was there nearly four years. I liked it there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's what you did 'til you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. That's right. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What were you in the butcher's place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh - I just helped out 'cos I wasn't very old you see, I wasn't - I weren
't old enough to - take responsibilities. I had to do what she told me to do, I had to help her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It was in the house rather than the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, in - oh yes, not in the shop, in the house. Helping her in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did you do in the doctors, were you a parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 maid there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, I was house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
maid, cook and washwoman and all sorts up there. I had to hurry up twelve o'clock and - and get changed, put in me black - me black dress and collar and cuffs and all the rest of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You said you had to have a certificate to begin with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, I did to leave school. You couldn't leave school without a certificate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That was to do with leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. That's right. Without that you couldn't leave school at thirteen, without your certificate you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time did you normally leave school then, about fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Fourteen they - they reckoned to leave school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was this normal for people who were going into service to get certificates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes. Yes
. Yes. Yes. Oh any amount did 'cos I mean to say wages wasn't very much, they was glad for children to - if it wasn't very much they're glad of a little bit of help you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you send the money home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I used to - I used to come home. Walk 
home from Ashburton you see. Every Sunday. I had every Sunday off and I used to walk home and my father used to take me back in the evening.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But you'd live in during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Live in during the week, yes. Yes. And at Moorside I was - I li
ved in altogether up - there. Then - but I had - I had half days off, you know, half a day on a Thursday and one alternate Sunday I had to stay and the other Sunday I had to go home because I was - there was a cook living there as well you see. But -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When you were still at school were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Seven o'clock every night. Every night, seven o'clock, if us wasn't in we'd we should hear it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you go to chapel early on a Sunday so that you'd still be in bed at seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, well - we used to go in at six then. So we used to be out at seven so we weren't much after our time Sunday evenings. But we always had - a little bit - of a drink of milk or something like that Sunday evenings you see. But other 
nights we didn't, we had a - good - good supper, and then we didn't have nothing else after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say the houses at Wollan and Charles had two rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What was the house at Landscome like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh that had got three bedrooms, and a - a sitting room and a kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So it was bigger than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, bigger - bigger, oh yes, different - different to - to - a real house up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Is that one of the reasons your father moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, oh no, it wasn't nothing to do with
 the house. He just wanted a change of scenery and a - change of - air and all of that I suppose. Just come in his mind that he wanted a change. There was nothing - nothing wrong, nothing, and the farmer that he worked for said, I'll give you twice as muc
h money if you'll stay on. So I mean you see it wasn't nothing to do with any - any fault nor nothing, he didn't want him to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would it seem a very long way to move across from North Devon to here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It is a long way. Good gracious me. First of a
ll we had to - in the morning we left up there in March - now in March the twenty-fifth - it was lovely moonlight the the night before. When we come to go in the morning 'twas - white with snow. We only had a pony and trap, we had to go seven miles in a p
o
ny and trap down to - down to Filley station. Filley. Filley station. You often hear about that on - you often hear about these places on the wireless - on the television you know. And - it was snowing like anything. Well then when we come down here, they
'd had snow but it's gone to slush and it was raining sleet when we arrived up here. I was sick all the way down. Oh it was a journey, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who would put you to bed in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Mother always put us to bed. Yes. Unless - she wasn't very w
ell or anything like that, then father would do it you see. But otherwise mother shouldered all responsibility of putting us to bed and seeing to us in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Which room would he whose, your parents would have one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh they had the - yes,
 they had one room and my brother had one room and - we two girls slept in one room you see. So - that's how we managed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh we had to bath in front of fire. Big bath - a big bath, yes, a big bath in front office. Every
 Saturday night we all had a - mother used to put - a copper - well I suppose you know what a copper is don't you, what you boil - light the fire in underneath, well they used to put that on going. Then we had plenty of - plenty of water. That one was out
doors, she had to go outdoors and fetch the water for that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 One of these outdoor pumps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that's right, that's right. Yes. Sometimes they would freeze up. What a fine caper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have clean clothes to put on after your bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes, yes, after - every Saturday night. Unless of course we went to Ashburton or - or - Buckfastleigh with father, well then we had a bath in the afternoon. We - we had to have a bath on Saturday. Always. Put on our clean clothes and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often would you go to Buckfastleigh or Ashburton on Saturday night, would it be every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh not every week. Say once - once in a - once a fortnight or once in three week perhaps. Just depends how - if - about father's hair for Ashburton you see. 'Cos he used to go into a man called Smith, up North Street, always went into him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 In the kitchen, we had them in the kitchen. Nice big kitchen it is you know. And they had a hearth fireplace, great big h
earth fireplace. Cor, we used to have lovely fires in there. Beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would all the family be present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Oh yes, all - all - all there for meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your father come back for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He used to come in the midday meal as well. So
metimes - I - I told you sometimes he used to go out on the top of those fields and he had to come all the way down here just to come home for an hour, he hadn't got hardly time to eat his dinner. Walk too in they days. Yes, they don't do it today, they'v
e got their tractors and all, it's a difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He had to be out by about six o'clock in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
He had be out before that, he had to be down in the stable by six o'clock mornings. Doing - to clean his horses and feed 'em up before he could take 'em round the field seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would he have for breakfast then, would he start off with anything before going out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well sometimes he would have porridge or - or - sometimes he wouldn't have nothing more than a bit of bread and bu
tter and some cake or bun sometimes. Just depends how he felt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But he would come back for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 No, he took bread and chee}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
se and - and - and have a - have cider for his - with his lunch, see, 'cos he - that was a privilege. Cider with some bread and cheese for their lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When would their lunch be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh about - ten o'clock to half past ten I expect. I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When would breakfast be for the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Eight o'clock. We always had it just before we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of thing would you have for breakfast?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh anything that was going. Sometimes it would be a boiled egg or - or porridge or and sometimes we didn't have more than bread and butter and cake, just depends what mo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 
ther could - had got you see. '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Cos you couldn't pick and choose in those days, you had just to have what was going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But a lot of the stuff you'd get would be grown in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes, the vegetables and that. Yes, vegetables. All grown in the garden, we didn't ever
 - never had to buy anything. We might have - father have bought potatoes sometimes if they've been a poor year and he hasn't had a very good crop. Us might have bought a few potatoes but never bought nothing else. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And - you say you had a pig?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, had a pig and salted it down, yes, or half of him any rate. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And you had chickens as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, chickens, we had chickens, we had eggs you see. We - we weren't - we were a lot better off than a lot of 'em, you see. But nearly ever
ybody kept a pig in those days. Nearly everybody. But not chi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 kens, they didn't all keep chickens, but - pigs, my goodness, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What other meat would you have, what about rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, plenty of rabbits. Plenty of rabbits you could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they be poached?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Trap 'em. Trap 'em. Yes. Used to put in wires. And trap 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often a week would you say you had meat to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well we only had - real meat on Sunday. A roast join on Sunday. But mother used to make up in - have a bi
t of stew, have some bones from the butcher and make up some stew and - different things like that during the week you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you ever have fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes, yes, 'cos the man used to come from Paignton. Called Joe - Jonas. And - of course you
 got - got a lot of money for sixpence in they days, lot of fish for sixpence in they days. They throw 'em at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 ee nearly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you ever have things like tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, never. Never. Never. No, weren't no such thing I don't believe. I never sa
w it. I don't think there was anything like that when we were brought up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would there ever be any occasions when you'd eat in another room to the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Oh - oh - might be if - if - now we used to take local preachers in to tea, when they come - if they come a journey, take it in turn}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 s. And - then - 'cos the table w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
asn't big enough for any more, we used to have it in - sitting in the front room then. If we had anybody special come in like that or - if - if the table wasn't big enough we'd 
go in the front room. That was all, but we always kept to the kitchen for all our meals else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time would you eat at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 One o' - oh, we used to start ours before one o'clock. But father used to be home one o'clock, because we had to be 
back in school half past one you see. And mother used to give us ours and then - then when father come in she'd see to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would you call the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 One o' - oh well, cook - mother cooked every day sometime. She made - made all the t
hings, I don't know how she used to do it but she used to make up - things. Buy bits of - bacon and boil, you know. If she hadn't got any of her own. But she mostly had that - some of pigs ears and pigs - trotters and all things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have these from the butchers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes, you can now but - we had our own then you see. 'Cos the butcher always used to give her back the - the - the - knuckles and - yes, yes, well he - he only just used to take what he - what he wanted, the - the carcass,
 but - the head and - half of the head and his - and his legs - feet and legs he used to give mother back. So it was very good, I mean, he just took the best parts of the pig now if you understand me. So we - she had plenty - plenty of meat if she salted 
it in you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It sounds a very nice set-up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It is. It was lovely. And dumplings and everything, of course it's beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When would your next meal be after lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh not until father came home, six o'clock. Or - or it would be half past six time he got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would you have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh mother used to fry - bacon, potato and - and - every night we had fry. Something or other, bacon and potato or bacon and egg or - whatever she got. She had - if she did have fish well w
e might have a bit of fish. But we always had a - we always had something like that in the evening 'cos I mean father was working he wanted something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that the last meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That was the last meal we had. So we had to make a good meal of it. Then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So the evening meal would be the main meal of the day would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well yes, I think it would be. I think it would be. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things would you drink with meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Nothing, I never - we didn't have anything to drink unless w
e - if it was it was water. But we always had a cup of tea afterwards. That was all. Yes, after a meal. That' right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have things like home made beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, nothing like that. No, no. There'd nothing like that done in - not in - I did it, not - when I was young any rate, I don't remember.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How about home made jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes. Mother made all her home made jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where would she get the fruit from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 From the garden. Garden. Gooseberries and strawberries and - raspberries and bla
ckcurrants. Then she used to make apple jelly with - when - we had an apple tree in the garden. And she used to make apple jelly. Yes, she used to make enough to last for a twelve month. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you were really very self-sufficient?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, well ye
s we were. I think we were better off in those days than what they are today. 'Cos people don't preserve today. They don't, they don't try to till their gardens, I mean it's disgrace some of 'em. But - for - they were - they used to till their gardens in 
those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Probably because they don't have to do so these days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no, they can get it. They can get it, you see, t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 
hat's what it is. 'Tis spoiled th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 em. But still I'd rather have fresh stuff than I would od}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893  tinned stuff any rate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever go blackberrying?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes. Yes. Yes, yes, rather. I've been out half past five in the morning for my father, he's - he was very fond of - of mushrooms. And I've been up half past five in the morning, and gone off over a field to get mushrooms for mo
ther to - do for dinner. Half past five in the morning you know. Do - you gotta go when d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893  - yes, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When would you eat dinner, what time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well, midday dinner, midday. Yes, midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Then you'd have tea about six o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that - that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did your mother cook in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
In the kitchen. In the - she had a little - American stove. It's a little stove stood in the corner, it's like - like the ordinary old fashioned stoves bu
t - the chimney used to come in to the - hearth, in the - in the - that in there. A dear little thing, it was lovely to cook by. She did all her ironing with that too. Well she used to take in washing, I told you. And she used to put all her irons on ther
e, get them hot. 'Cos you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I thought you meant doing the ironing on the actual stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh no, no, no, no, no, no, no, she - used to heat the irons on that stove. 'Cos they didn't get so dirty as they did putting them down in front of - fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your mother ever make her own medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Only senna}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7044898\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
pods and - and Epsom Salts. Yes. Yes, that's all. She - we used to have that three mornings and stop three mornings - purify the blood she said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did she get that idea from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well old fashioned - oh it was from her mother and they I suppose in younger - other days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did it I work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes. It kept you fit you know. Oh yes it did. Purifies the blood, I mean, that's - that's the main thing if you're blood's all right isn't it. I didn't used to like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long did you keep on taking that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Three mornings - three mornings and - oh say about three weeks. Three weeks off, then we'd stop, see. Then - perhaps start again, see how - see how we was I suppose. But that was - that was a stand-by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Can you ever remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you ever remember your father having more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No, we were all shared alike. Of course we children didn
't have so much because we were - we were only children but - father - father and mother, they - they had - they was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were you ever allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. Not likely. If we did they'd see, 'ere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We had to have what was put on our plates. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would happen if you left something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh had to have it for tea. I told you about the pea soup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You refused to have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I did, and when mother was upstairs I went out and - buried it in the garden. Oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did she ever find out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, she never found out. No she never found out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would have happened if there was something on the table you wanted like the salt would you just reach for it or did you ask for it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no, you had to ask to be passed to us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, we could ask for a second helping.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, my goodness. Very strict at meals they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who taught you that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Both of them, both of them. One didn't up hold us and another - you know, scold us, they both worked together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Could you bring a book or a toy to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No fear. Oh no, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not until they finished. Unless - something urgent we had to - we had to be back a certain time at school
 or anything. Well then that would be different. But never - never - never - teatime we couldn't leave the table. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of joints would you have on a Sunday, would it be beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Beef or - lamb. But we had pork you see. It would be one of
 those. Or you used to have a - good old joint of - beef - for half a crown. Mother had a great big piece of - for - for half a crown in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time of day would you have it on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Had it about quarter to one, Sundays, because we went to chapel you see and - if we went in Staveton we'd have to leave early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Your father wouldn't have to work at all on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He'd got to go down and do his horses. Yes, feed 'em, feed 'em. And feed 'em again - he used to go in again after 
- we came home from chapel four o'clock, and feed 'em again and bed 'em up for the night. Oh yes, twice a day he had to go down there Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would he be there for breakfast on Sundays or would he still be out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He - he'd be home for breakfast, 
because he used to go down early you see. Be home for breakfast, about eight o'clock we used to have breakfast Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about tea on Sunday, would that be earlier or later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We - we used to have that about quarter to five - Sundays.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did all the family sit at the table for their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who would sit at the head of the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Mother. Father would sit on the - the side of the table, near mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who did the carving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How was the meal served, who would serve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well she used to have dishes in those days and put 'em in on the table. Everything on the table in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What order would you be served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - she used to do father first, because he had to get back you see, and - then - well us children and then herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did the younger brother and sister sit before they could feed themselves, do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well my sister used t
o have a little high chair and sit by mother. And - my brother sat next and I'd sit down the bottom of the table. All sit at the table. Oh yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Very very nice person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did she show much affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 If you had any worries could you take them to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
I could. Of course we could. Yes, she was always willing to hear - and try to help us. I mean, when I was old I - troubles I've had I've - I've spoken to mother about it and she's always helped me. Yes, I had a good mother - and father.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was your father the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We had to behave in a proper manner. No answering back. And - and - 
speak in a proper manner. And - what - do what we could to help them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things do you think they brought you up to think were right things to believe in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well they brought us up to believe in God. If we told a lie, well - we -
 we had to go in and stand on a stool, I told you didn't I, stand on a stool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You were telling me about when you knocked a table over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Oh - oh, well one night we were playing, it was in the winter, we were playing and - 'course - they'd got
 a table, mother had a got a cloth on it you see. We were playing and I - of course I - I pulled the tablecloth and pulled the lamp off. Oh I - didn't I have a hiding. Nearly caught the place afire. It was my fault, yes, I - I - I mean I - they - and I - 
I didn't - they didn't do it because I did disorder, I did disorder because I'd no business there. No business under the table. Still - soon got over it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were you punished very often or was that just a rare occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh - no, we were punished if 
we done anything wrong. Yes. We couldn't answer back nor anything - in those days. My goodness me. They were strict. And we weren't to - allowed to go out with any bad children that, you know, that swore or - anything, they wouldn't let us go out with tho
se - them. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there anybody around like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, there were, plenty. Plenty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who would punish you, was it both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Both of 'em w
ould do it. Yes. Father - father wouldn't do it unless he jolly - well had to do it, and then he'd use the buckle strap you see. But mother would - punish us by standing us on a stool in the corner, that's how she used to punish us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That was in the sitting room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that's right. Looking at the - looking at a bare wall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long would you have to stand on that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Hour. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Or was one more strong that the other maybe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, both the same. And I can remember my grandmother teaching me to say my prayers. Home at Loollen. I remember - I can remember as plain as anything. Poor thing. She came with us down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you say grace before meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No. No, we didn't say grace before meals. That's one thing we didn't do. I suppose it wasn't so much done in those days as it is today but that - they do today I know and I do always now but - they never thought about it, I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would they consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - we - he - he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would that be Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well, yes, or evenings sometimes if father was home - before we went to bed, and - 
'cos he used to pray out of his head, he didn't have no prayer book nor nothing. Then we had to say the Lord's Prayer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time of day would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well say about - half past six, seven o'clock. Every night, if - if he was home in time, becau
se sometimes - with horses or anything you don't know you see, he - he wasn't sure time he - but that was the time he was supposed to leave work, six o'clock. But sometimes there was things - well unforeseen that he had to - stay - or go down again or sta
y
 down there you see to see to it. So then - we didn't used to do it then. But we always had to say our prayers before we went into bed. Every night. Yes. Mother - mother - mother taught us those mostly when - from - from when - we used to have to kneel do
w
n in front of her. When we were - well - to - I can't remember myself but Gertie, that's my sister, she wasn't two year old and she used to - kneel down and she used to chatter away, she didn't know - she didn't know no sense to it but she used to chatter
 away what we were doing you see. Yes. Put her hands together, dear little thing too. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Can you remember anything like a birthday, what would happen on a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh we never - we never - had anything on birthdays, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No cards or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, my goodness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would anything special happen on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, we had a Christmas Day was a - a Christmas pudding or a few crackers and a few nuts and - few oranges, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have stockings or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
We hung up stockings but - we didn't get much in 'em, that's all we got in 'em was orange and few sweets perhaps or something like that. And in the end - my father - my father put lumps of coal in 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have any friends round or neighbour or anything like that on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No, no. They didn't - they'd do to keep their own houses then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would Christmas Day be a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. You never had no holiday. I mean - it was like a Sunday for father you see. And - they never had 
Boxing Day off, anything in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You didn't have Ban Holidays in those days, nothing like that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever have things like paid holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No. See if you wanted to have a day off you'd have to lose it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would he not have any holidays at all, without pay?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So he'd be working practically all the year round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, he was, he was, he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Used to have an accordi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8604912\charrsid1131893 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 n. Yes. Used to play that sometimes and we used to sing - of a Sunday, that would be of a Sunday. Hymns. Hymns. Sankeys as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Is that American hymns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well, it is - they do - they do use them - we used them a lot in the Methodist church years ago too. I showed you the book didn't I? Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have anybody in to sing with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Just us. Just us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who would play the accordi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8604912\charrsid1131893 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 n?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Father, yes, he used to play lovely too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your mother play the accordi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8604912\charrsid1131893 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 n?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, she had a - she had - like an accordi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8604912\charrsid1131893 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 n but 'twas - what did we used to call that one? Concertina. That's right, she used to play concertina. She could play too. She used to play hymns, sometimes she'd play 'em if she - it was wet or anything and to keep us 
in used to play it then, us used to sing - hymns then, children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8604912\charrsid1131893 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 s hymns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you ever do anything like sing folk songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no, nothing - nothing - not then in those days. No, nothing like that was allowed. They were very strict then, I mean - 
too strict, too strict, they were too strict really. Well of course really I mean to say 'cos I - I don't see no harm in the folk songs or anything today, but they were never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did they think was wrong with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I don't know what they thought was wrong with 'em. They said they're the devil's work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So when you made music together as a family it would be mainly hymns?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Hymns, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you all sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, we all sang. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your parents play any games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We used to play ludo sometimes. Snakes and ladders. Games like that in those days, we used to play that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you play them on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, not a Sunday. Not Sundays. We -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were they strict about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Saturday 
afternoon perhaps - when - father was home, father and mother was home - we - if it was wet or cold or anything like that we'd sit around the fire and - then we'd play the games like that. But otherwise we didn't. We didn't trouble about it, not on - 'cos
 we were always out to play you see. We used to go out to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things did you play outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
All kind - all kinds of things. Get some old pieces of short and pretend they were shops and pick off some stuff and pretend it was grocerie
s and that. Different things like that. Make - we made our own fun. Or played ball, hopscotch we used to play. Things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever have a bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not until I was - oh - I'd been at service two years before I had a bike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would there be no neighbours around at the top there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
There was plenty of children but they didn't used to - we didn't used to play together 'cos - you see, this place is scattered, as you see it is scattered. But the neighbours next door - we used to play with
. That's all we - and we used to go in that - over in the churchyard - over in - over on the allotment place where it's open. There was an old tree there we used to go up and play up in that one. Hide and seek and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many children did the neighbours have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Nine.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were they all about your age or sort of scattered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well the oldest one was the same age as me, oldest one. And the youngest one was - no, the youngest one's in Staveton, next to the youngest is down shop, that - that's - that's the one that's in shop, Miss Withers. That's the one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did - they ever come in to play ludo and things with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you go round to their house to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, we used to go in there as well, yes. Yes. Oh yes. Yes, we used to amuse ourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember if there were many books or newspapers or magazines in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - we used to have the Western Times and - mother used to have the Christian Herald.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often did they come out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Every - every Saturday I think it was. That was all we used to have. Then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And you'd have church books and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember your mother or father reading much in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well they didn't ha
ve much time to read in the week. Father used to read - Sundays - between the - the dinner and going to chapel in the afternoon, that's only time he had to read I think, and then that was the Bible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember whether they read much to you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
They used to. Yes. Mother would read of a evening. And - father would if he was home but - as I say, he wasn't always home of a evening, he - if he didn't - as I said if he didn't go down - if he didn't finish his - what he wanted to do he had to g
o down again after tea you see. So - and then perhaps be somewhere about eight o'clock before he came home and we would be in bed then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things would she read, would this be Bible stories an things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - we - mother used to have a 
nice book of Bible stories. And she used to read us them. But I - I gave them to my grandchildren now that one 'cos it was - 'twas lovely stories. You know, simple.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you get books from the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. I got ever so many prizes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often did you get given prizes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Once a year. Once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that for attendance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. And for answering Bible questions you see, answering scripture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When would they do that, would that be during Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, j
ust during the Sunday school, they'd have that just before - Christmas. And then Christmas they used to give us our - rewards as they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would everyone get a prize?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Only those - only those that answered. Only those that answered the ques
tions. Then we used to have outings you see. A outing every year. To the - to Paignton or - or - Teignmouth in those days. The - four-in-hand, in a - have you seen them, four-in-hand? It was - it was like a great long - carriage with seats each side, and 
a
 - and up in the front, you've seen on them the pictures I expect, two men sitting up in front. And - and the four - four - four horses. We used to have those and to take us for outings down to Paignton and - or Teignmouth. For the day. Once a year, that'
s in June. June - June as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long would you be there for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 All day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time of day would you have to set off to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Seven o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What happened if it rained?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh it was awful when it - well they - they had - a cover to go over, if it was raining, used to be able to put a cover over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But you'd go come rain or shine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. We'd go. Because we were all right, we had relatives in Paignton so we if it was wet we could go there for the day yo
u see. But Teignmouth we didn't have nobody.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The parents went along with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, all - all of us. All of us. Used to have two of those - carriage - carriage things you see. It was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So how many children would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh we - we'd have between thirty and forty children in the summer school then. So that'll tell you. Was a fair - yes, yes. Was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It must have been quite a procession?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It was. It was. And - when we come to - Orley Hill, we had to walk up Warley Hill, 
and we had to help push the things up Warley Hill. That's right, that's true. That's between - Avilpain and Newton. You don't know that way do you? Bonhampston, do you know Bonhampston at all? Well you go through Bonhampston. And then - well you don't kno
w nothing about Bonhampston so I can't explain to you. Go right through Bonhampston then, and then you come to Warley Hill, that's the first place you come to, Warley Hill after you leave -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's a very steep hill is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh my goodness me it is steep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time would you come back, would you come back in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Seven o'clock. Get back here by seven. Yes, back by seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long would it take to get there by horse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh - hour and a half I expect. Of course we didn't used to stop anywhere, we used to go straight there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they arrange picnics and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
We used to have a tea in the Sunday - chapel Sunday school. The Methodist Sunday school now they call it, the Methodist. They all had - all had - the
y always had a tea ready for us. Same down at Teignmouth. Lovely tea. And after tea we used to - just prepare to come home again. Go round and see what us wanted to see more and come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It would be a very rare occurrence to go to the seaside?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh that's only time we had - we could go. We never - couldn't go then in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It's only about fifteen miles away isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. I know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were - you mentioned a funeral in the family didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Grandmother's funeral. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember much about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, I do remember it. We came down in - we came down here in March. And - grandmother died in May, sixth of May.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was your grandfather dead by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He was dead, he was - he was buried up Charles. 
Where he was - I told you he was a - yes, that's right, and - she died in May, she had Haemorrhage and died. It was awful shock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were there many people at the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, no, only - they didn't - we weren't known. You see, we weren't known at a
ll. Only coming here in March you see. Only or - our own relatives come or - mother's brother and - and some from Paignton that - ordinary cousins from Paignton. But to do with my grandmother. But - that was awful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have things like hearses or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Carried her by hand then. Eight bearers they used to have in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would the bearers be relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. Well - men from the distance, working men from the - from the - from around here you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you go back to the house afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We came back home again, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have anything like mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes. It was all - you used to be draped in those days, oh my, veils and all it was, horrible. Good job that's gone out. Oh it was morbi
d. Yes. I don't know how they used to like it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It would be quite an effort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, just - you couldn't do it. Couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were you ever taken shopping, you say you went to Ashburton and Buckfastleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes - with father and mother, wherever, you know - which one they went to. We often gone in there like that with them. But not else.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That would always be on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, Saturday evening. Yes, 'cos the shops used to stay open 'til nine, ten o'clock in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You did go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember any other outings with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Only Sunday school outing, only Sunday school, yes, that's all. Never went anywhere else from - one twelve months to the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you wouldn't go for any holidays or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. It was out of the question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you ever play between coming back from school and going to bed, would there be much time left between those times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well - not very much. 'Cos we always had to wash the dishes up you see. And - and tidy up before we went to bed. Then we all - all had to have a jolly good wash and do up 
our hairs and that - that took a bit of time. No, I didn't - we didn't go out after. 'Cos you had to be in bed by seven.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have different clothes to wear on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, we had a best frock. Well we - we - we girls had a best frock and
 my brother had a best suit of - a little best suit of clothes. Well that had to last us for three or four year. Couldn't have no new. But we always wore hob nail boots, always, Sundays and Saturdays too. On Sunday. Yes. We did have different clothes to w
ear on Sunday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 This was the Methodist chapel you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Methodist, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often would your parents go on Sunday, would it be twice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Twice - twice, afternoon evening. 'Cos the Sunday school in the morning, my father used to go
 in the morning - whether he's going to preach - going preaching, 'cos he used to preach you see, sometimes he'd have to go a little more, well he couldn't take a service then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So he wouldn't just preach in the local area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He goes - he went all over the place. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How would he travel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
By pony - and trap. In those days. And sometimes he'd have to walk out Buckfastleigh to pick up the pony and trap. Or out Buckfast. Which way - went to Staveton he'd to - he'd go to Buckfast, but
 it is - any other way where he had to go, he'd have to go to Buckfastleigh and pick up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was he a lay preacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Lay preacher, lay preacher. Lay preacher. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long was he doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Forty-seven year. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your mother ever go out with him on those occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No. No, no. No. Because other preachers used to with him you see, and - of course the trap there was only room for two or three, you see, when they got one sit at the back, there was only room for two or three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would he be away every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Not every Sunday. Oh he wouldn't - he wouldn't take it on every Sunday. He couldn't do that. Be too much for him. Well say once - once a - about once a quarter. Because he had - no, it wouldn't be too often. '
Cos I mean he had the Sunday school too, he was superintendent of the Sunday school you see besides that. He was a busy man. Then he - we used to have prayer meetings in the middle of the week. And we - I - I used to go to them but the other ones used to 
have to go to bed but I was allowed up a bit later that night. Thursday evening to go to prayer meetings.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who would look after the other two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Mother. Mother stay home, yes, she stayed home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were there any other social activities organised by the chapel, apart from the outing and this prayer meeting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, only - only - Sunday school, when we used to have our Sunday school Anniversary. We were all given a tea then. That was the only time - that we used to have anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Once a year. First Sunday in May. Anniversary of the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The setting up of the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that's right, that's right, that's right. Used to go on the platform then and have special hymns, we children used to
 sing special hymns then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often did you go to Sunday school on a Sunday, was it twice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, once in the morning. And church - then chapel - in the afternoon and evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you belong to the choir at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 There weren't no choir. N
o choir. I know once - one Sunday evening we had the preacher from Totnes - and - I was sickening for the measles and I - I went to sleep in chapel. And he - he said, don't take any notice of that child, he said. Listen to me. Poor man, he's dead now. Oh 
dear. I was - I was - I - no, I was pickled the next morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have any of these sort of hell and brimstone people coming round, like you hear about these fiery preachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No. Not in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the chapel run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, we didn't have anything like that. Wasn't no - nobody there to superintend, my father wouldn't know nothing about that you see. And - and Mr Giles, he's Head, he - he didn't know nothing about it. No, we never had nothing like that in our church.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you belong to any other club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Can you remember whether your parents took any political attitudes in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you mean voting or anything like that? Yes, yes, he used to take a - mot
her didn't but father did, 'cos - because women didn't vote in those days. Father used to. Used to - he used to have to vote at Staveton - to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's about two mile isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Two mile and a half, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would he get time off to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, he'd have to go after they come home from work. After - about eight, nine o'clock, used to go down. Walk down Staveton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you know what way he voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh I didn't used to ask him. That was secret.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever say anything about politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Never. Never mentioned it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 In some places men felt they risked their jobs if they voted different to the employer, do you remember anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was he ever a member of a political party at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
When your parents were not at work how did they spend their time, your father would spend an awful lot of time in religious activities I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Religion and gardening and things - and - things like that. Mother used to pass her time with sewin
g, she used to do a lot of sewing you see. She'd always have - have a - had got a needle or something. Doing something for somebody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say she took in dressmaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes. And laundry work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She never went out to enjoy herself on her own or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Goodness me, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 There wasn't a women's Institute or anything like that around? You say your father got home about six to half past six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that's - that's right, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And he used to go out once a week to the prayer meeting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would he ever go anywhere else during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. He was glad to be home and sit down and rest after he came home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever attend any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 There was nothing like that here. Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How about pubs or things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever attend races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He wouldn't bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he belong to anything like a boot club or a sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Nothing. Nothing like that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did you get on with your brother and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Me? Fine. Yes I - I used to be a mother to them you see. Yes. I had to look after them. See they didn't get into no mischief and that.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they ever get into any trouble when you had to bail them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh well - only just childish things I mean, 't weren't nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You can't remember anything really serious happening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Nothing really bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I suppose you felt closer to your sister than your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, I used - I used to be very fond of me brother. Yes. Cor yes, I - I wouldn't have anything happen to him, I - if anything - if he was - in trouble I used to cry like anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he ever get in any scrapes himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well he was knocked off a bicycle once - knocked down by a bicycle once, that was only time that he was - in anything I can remember. Like that, I know I cried like anything then 'cos he was - he was really hurt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You said some of the children round the neighbourhood used to swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes they did. They did, some of 'em. It was dreadful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, when I went to school. But - the schoolmaster 
was very strict, if he - if - if he heard 'em he - he'd make 'em a thousand words - thousand words. Yes. Thousand. Yes. I've had to do that before now when I've misbehaved myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things did you have to write out a thousand times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He - he put in - he put in something - what you had to write, and you had to write that a thousand times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you do that in school hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He caught - he caught me - well I was called in once when I went up to school, as I went up to school I w
as called in and that's what I had to do. And I was kept in in the playground and kept in when - when they was going home from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What had you done wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I - I forget it, I don't know what - I don't know what I'd done. Oh he was strict tha
t - Mr Collier was strict but my goodness he was a good teacher. I've been stood in the corner up there more than once.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How was he good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Good teacher. He was a good teacher. But he was strict. Coo my goodness, you - you had to obey him. He tann
ed my brother - one - once he tanned my brother - he black mark him. And mother took it up and let him see it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What do you mean a black mark, on his body?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, on his bottom. On his bottom. He couldn't sit. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he have a stick or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He had a stick - a cane. A cane and he - he put him - used to put 'em across his knee and tan 'em like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would he ever do that to the girls as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, he used to cane the girls. Cane the girls on the hand and put 'em in the corn
er. That's what he used to do to the girls, or - or make 'em write out words - those words was worse than standing in the corner. Because you couldn't go out to play you see, you had to stop in after the others gone home, it was terrible that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many schoolteachers would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have the one all the time or did you change as you grew older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When I was in a classroom I had his wife you see, she was a teacher in the classroom. And they used to have a - a young girl
 - to teach the very small ones, babies just started. Used to start at three then in they days. And - then when you got old enough used to go out in the big room - with Mr Collier you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How old would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Seven year old I think when we went in the big room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you started school when you were three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, I did. Before I was three when home because I used to go with mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 This was when you were still in Charles or Wollan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So when you moved to Staveton you'd go straight into the big class?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
At - at - no, I didn't, I was - I was twelve months in the classroom. 'Cos I - I wouldn't - didn't leave in the big one, I was six year old when I come down here you see and - and I moved in the big room when - about seven just about twelve months after.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things did he expect you to observe, did he expect you to be on time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 My goodness yes. If you weren't on time he - he'd be waiting for you at the door with his cane. And sometime
s you couldn't always help it. I know one morning mother was ill - and - oh and I didn't know what it was but she was having a baby. And - I had to go - come down here, into - down to Beara, in down the bottom. And I was a bit late going up. Cor didn't he
 give me the stick. He wouldn't listen to what I told him. No. So - whoever was in the house, I don't know who it was in the house, going up to him and told him. He - he apologised after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He didn't ask first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, he didn't ask. He didn't ask, he said I - hold out your hand. He was waiting at the door. Didn't he give me the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That sounds a bit ruthless doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were you ever given any lessons by your parents before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. They didn't know much in those days, I mean to say they weren't - not like it is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they ever ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, they used to ask us. Father knew more about the Bible than anything else, he used to ask us well round ab
out the Bible, he was always keen on the Bible you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you get much Bible tuition at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes. Yes. My goodness, I had - I don't know how many certificates for answering questions on the Bible. My sister had a big gold one from when she was there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was this at the Sunday school or the ordinary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, the - the ordinary school. The - the - the head - inspector - at Christmas - Bible Inspector used to come down and give us - examination of the Bible. And - all the chapel
 people - knew more than the church people did. And they couldn't understand it. Why the chapel people could answer so well. 'Cos church - I don't expect the church people was ever taught really like we were. We were taught the Bible, we had to - we had t
o remember it you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would there be anybody else come round to test you on anything else other than the Bible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not - not in the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have exams and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, we had - we had - oh - yes, we had a - 
inspector - come round and he used to take English and geography and songs. I weren't very good in geography I might tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He'd come from outside the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Come from - he'd come from Exeter. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Once a year. What they calls the examinations, the exams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would it be oral or would it be written?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
He used to put it on the - he used to put the questions on the blackboard. And we had to answer the questions what was put on the blackboard. So many question
s, see. And so many songs would be put on the blackboard, it would all be put on the Blackboard. Then we had to do what - we had to write it down, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would happen if you didn't do very well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well we failed. We failed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would happen if you passed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We'd go in a higher standard then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many standards were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Seven. And Ex-seven. Seven and ex-seventh. And there was two boys - I don't know whether I told you that - two boys up there, one's -
 they gave - he gave them a sum to do. And - 'twas a difficult sum. They did it, and the schoolmaster couldn't do it. No, he couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So what happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They - so they -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It made the schoolmaster look a fool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. It did. B
ut they - they went in the ex-seventh you see then. And then - and one of 'em, he - he was - you'd think he was a lazy old thing. He'd lie like this on the desk instead of doing his work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Didn't the schoolmaster tick him off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No. He didn't. He didn't used to. Coo he was a - he looked a lazy thing but my God he - he had the brains any rate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What happened to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well I don't know what - I believe he went in the Police force. He was called Clegg. He were in - well he's good tall 
chap. I believe - I - I think he went in - in the Police force and - the other one, he's dead. He - he lived out Buckfastleigh, he was called Crimp. He lived up Dene. I don't know whether the place is still there now though where they used to live. I'll a
sk Jack when he comes here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did the teachers feel about manners and speaking properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh you had to learn your manners. We had to curtsey to him in the road. Boys had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 To the schoolmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Schoolmaster or anybody, anybody -
 bit higher than we were. We had to courtsey to them and - and - and the boys had to touch their hats to them and - yes sir and no sir and yes ma'am and no ma'am, oh my goodness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were there people you'd call proper gentlemen or real ladies?
