\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were there any theatres in Buckfastleigh or Ashburton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. I can't remember, I don't know - I can't remember so long ago as that now. Don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I don't know whether there was a picture house, there might have been a picture house that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You didn't go to it though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever go to anything like a concert, any village concerts in Staveton or anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, we used to have concerts here sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well - people would come - our own people would get up a - a kind of a - what can I say - entertainment, different things. Singing and - playing the piano and - playing the violin and things like that, up in our school we've had that before now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often would that happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh not very often. Not very often. No, not very often. In and out. Because they were all working, I mean they hadn't got time to prepare themselves you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would the chapel organise that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. The - the - the village would organise that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The Parish Council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they have people from outside come down as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Only - only the village people. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your father ever go along and play the accordi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16581357\charrsid1131893 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 n?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No, he n
ever went to that. Well he didn't used to have time to go, not in the evening, it was in the evenings you see and he didn't used to go out, he didn't used to go to anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your parents give you any pocket money when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We had to give it to them what we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 There weren't any ways you would go around and earn any money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No, no, there wasn't anywhere like that. Never done anything outside the home before I went in service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Can you remember anyone outside the home ever helping your mother to look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No relatives or friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about when you said your mother was sick and you were a bit late for school, would anyone come in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well that was - that was - no, that - that - that was - when - like when she was having a baby. Well that lady used to look after then you see. What - what came - what I fetched down here. She went and looked after her then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would she be a midwife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That was the only time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Can you remember your mother being ill at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well she was always getting ill. And I - when I got old enough I had to stay home from school, had a certificate
 then again - to stay home from school to look after her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you'd be the one who helped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes, I'd be the main one. Was the main one. I used to know so much then - as I do now in - in the way of things really. I was brought up to do it and I used to do it properly too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did the teachers think of it, were they the ones who gave you the certificate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well they had to. They had to. They were very good, I mean, they - they - they know mother was ill you see and - and the Vicar was 
very good, they was very good, the Vicar and his wife. Used to make up little meals for mother and - things different. She had pleurisy very bad once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So the village sort of mucked in to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, yes. They were very very kind people in thos
e days. Different to what they are today I tell you, they don't know you today. All got these old cars and they - they just pass you, don't - although you've been neighbours they don't - don't recognise you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the neighbours come in very much in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they have an invitation or would they just pop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Just pop in and see, just pop in and say, have you brewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they have cups of tea and things like that all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, no cups of tea, they didn't used to have no cups of tea. Just come in to have a talk that's all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your parents have many relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Nobody. Nobody, only Paignton that's all. That was \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Your parents came from the other side of Devon didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, North Devon. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So would you see your relatives very often then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, my goodness me. Years and years before we saw any of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So it was mainly neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Neighbours that - yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your parents have many friends in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What, in the village? Yes, they was all friendly, every one of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where would they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - meet 'em at the chapel or perhaps - if we - say we were going out for 
anything anywhere. Just for walks, sometimes we used to go for a walk, and - we may meet up with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16581357\charrsid1131893  'em then and then we'd have a m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
atter - or mother would. But she didn't visit nobody out of the village, only her neighbour used to come in and see her you see every day. She used to come in, shouted up the stairs every morning to mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Did they share the same friends by and large do you remember, did your father have any special friends of his own or your mother have her own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. They were - they were all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were there any occasions when you would have neighbours in for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh my goodness, no. No, couldn't afford that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say they'd call in casually without an invitation by and large?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your parents often go out to visit friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It was mainly when you went out that you met them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right. Just - coincidence if you did meet 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would anybody ever come back after chapel for instance?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. 
Only - only the local preachers, that's all. Come and have a cup of tea, that's all would - that's all would come. And that weren't always, we used to take it in - they used to take it in turns you see who had them. And the man who used to play the organ,
 he used to go from Buckfast every Sunday. He was called Bessel. He lives down near the Abbey. He used to go every Sunday. And - he always used to he used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Twice a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He used to stay here, he used to come in the afternoon and stay 'til the 
evening and then we - they used to take him in turn to tea you see. And - every Sunday he used to bring sweets, little packets of sweets - for all us children. So after the service was over we always used to trot up to the organ for a packet of sweets.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember your parents getting together with friends and neighbours to play games or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh my goodness me no. Couldn't think about - games in they days, there was too much work to be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And when they played music it was only for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right. That was only Sundays when he used to play the accordi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16581357\charrsid1131893 o}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 n. Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did your mother play the concertina during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, Sundays, that was Sundays too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 People divide society into different grou
ps or classes in those days, before 1918 did you think of some coming from one group or class and others from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well we used to think those who'd got money was better than us in those days, that's the ones we had to bow and - touch our hats to
, but otherwise we were all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well one used to - one person used to live up Thorneycroft, and the - and the schoolmaster and - the parson we had to do it to. Anybody who had a bit of money, say that way. We always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So it was based on money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of people would you say belonged to the same group as yourselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Poor people. Just like ourselves, poor people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who would be considered the most important people in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh the - the Vicar. The Vicar was the most important one in our village. We always looked on him as - being the head of the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I don't think there was anybody else here, not - not that took 
an interest in us, in the church - village like he did. He was the only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about the schoolteacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh he didn't used to visit. The Vicar used to visit everybody. He did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would he come round very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. My goodness, once a
 twice a week he'd been you know. Yes. And if you was sick he'd be there. He saved my father's life - when he had pneumonia. Well - the doctor couldn't find out what was the matter with him. And one Sunday night after church he came down and he - and - it
 was - I don't know what - what's that stuff they call they used for - yes, it 't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16581357\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
wasn't - no, we poulticed him, penicil - I don't know if it is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16581357\charrsid1131893 penicillin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
. Any rate he came down and he - he told mother to get some hot water. Mother got some hot water and h
e put this up to my father. And it brought - brought the pneumonia so that they could see it. They couldn't see it because it was so embedded in, and they couldn't find out what was the matter with him. And - and - so he rung up the doctor and told him wh
a
t he had done - or - or asked him if he could - do it or something, he done it. And you know that saved my father's life. And that was only through his thrashing. The dust had got in his lungs - you know, the dust from the thresher, got in his lungs and i
t - was at the back of the lung. And they couldn't find it out you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was the Vicar practicing medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well he - I don't know - he was very good in medicine, I don't know - he - he didn't practice it but he - he knew. He knew, he - he -
 he was ever so good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was the vicar a local man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes, he - he lived for years. He died of cancer in the end poor fellow. Poor this. He was nice - they - they were nice people those were. Good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What group would the people like shopkeepers belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well some was chapel and some was church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of social group did they belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh they'd be only like ourselves, we could talk to them like we talk to you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We had - we had to sir the farmers. Father had to sir -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What group would they belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Aristocracy. Yes sir, no sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What sort of people would you say went to church and what sort of people went to chapel, was there any distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, no - none at all. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in any ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not really. 'Cos we all - they - they was always the same. 'T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16581357\charrsid1131893  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 weren't different one day than another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where you lived would you say all the people in the working cla
ss group had the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups amongst them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No. Oh perhaps the - the ones who got a bit of money had a bit better food but the the poor, my goodness they were poor. Some of 'em couldn't get same
 as we had. If they had a family, like I told you, this one with the nine year - nine children, well that's - that's a lot of mouths to feed isn't it. They couldn't have it like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, they had a garden, he used to ti
ll the garden. But I mean - 'twas a lot, nine, and only thirteen shillings a week you know, he didn't have no - we didn't have no - extra money coming in. 'T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16581357\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 was hard does in those days. Well he - they used to keep pigs too and chickens, they used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did people have large families in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, they did, they did. Good gracious, some had thirteen and - ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 In this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. The one down here in this house had ten, down the bottom house. Ten children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16581357\charrsid1131893 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 ope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
I don't know how they used to manage. They must slept - top to bottom in the beds for certain. They must have done. Because - only two bedrooms down there they had ten children. I don't know how they managed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You don't think that one group felt superior to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, nothing like that. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about craftsmen or skilled workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
That was never thought of. Never thought of in those days. 'Tis all farm labouring you see. And nothing like - yes, oh 'twas all farm labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you think your mother and father had the same attitude to people in different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Just the same. In fact - everybody was the same. You all - all classed each other as the same then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about the people who had the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh well they had - they were different, a bit different, of course they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was it possible to move from one group to another, could you work your way up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Weren't nothing to do to work your way up in they days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You do remember people being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, well that - that - there is those, I mean, I've just told you about the - the Vicar and - and Miss B
artlett. Well she was a lady that - that'd - used to live up where - what I told you about maybe - wanted to - summons me, have a policeman come for me. She used to live up in that school one time. And she moved in - out to - out to Moorside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you 
find that was a rare thing amongst those kind of people or did that happen quite a bit? Was that the only real trouble you had when you were in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's - that was all I ever had. But there were those who - who - were at service capers, in a l
ot of places what I - when I told 'em, well they said, I've had that done to me. But - I didn't stay there after that very long, I give a month's notice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who got you this first job, that wasn't your first one was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You went to the one in Ashburton to begin with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 A baker called Poke, Baker Poke. He said, I know where your maid can go, he said. In butcher Halls's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who did he say that to, to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, mother. Yes. So then we walked in Ashburton and see this person
, I wondered where I was going to. But any rate I did go in there and I stayed there twelve months. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What was it like leaving home for the first time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I cried the first night. 'Cos I - I had to go right in the attic to sleep away from them, oh lonely I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many people were there there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Only him and her, the butcher and his wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many servants were there, just you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Only me. I - I used to have the work the - have to help the lady you see, in - do the hous
ework. 'Twasn't hard work, I mean, I wasn't - 'twas just doing the same as she was doing as you might as a matter of fact, dusting and - washing the dishes and cleaning up floors and that, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did many shopkeepers have servants in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, nearly everybody. They did. In those days. 'Course I mean they could have 'em for nothing pretty near then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you apply for the second job or did you hear about that as well, the one at Moorside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I - I used to go up with th
is - the servant, the cook. I used to go up with her sometimes, instead of coming home I used to go up with her. And - so Mrs Bartlett come out one day and asked me if I would like to come up there to live. So I though to myself, well 't}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16581357\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 would be nice to go up - with a friend of mine, 'cos I knew her you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that a bigger house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh gracious me - about ten bedrooms and - four or five - six down - downstairs rooms. And - and a kitchen. 'T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280546\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 was two houses in one you see, really, but - old Lady 
Bartlett used to call hers one - and the - the son used to call his the other, but you could walk into each other's places. And I was in charge of the old lady's you see. And - I - she said, would you like to come here? And I said, yes, so - I went up the
re. And I was happy up there for - three or four years. Three years I think I stayed up there. And I went, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many servants would there be up at Moorside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - only - only we two, the cook and - and me, house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280546\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280546\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 maid. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many people lived at the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The old lady - and - her son and his wife and daughter, they had a daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the son live next door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - he lived in the same house really. And he lived in one part you see, but he di
d - he could go - we could go through you see, they had a - they had a partition a - a knock down that we could walk from one house to the other see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you look after the whole house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I - I - no, the cook used to look after - her son, th
at part of the house, and I used to look after the old lady in that part of the house. And she had a nurse to look after her as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But she lived on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She lived on her own. Yes, she had - she used to have - no, she didn't go in with her
 son, she was on her own in her own house. Only time they - went together was prayers at night. She always had prayers at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you'd do the cooking for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You were a sort of jack of all trades?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I was there. House}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280546\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280546\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 maid and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you ever remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, plenty of policemen. Plenty of policemen in those days there were. On beat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did people think of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Afraid of 'em. Afraid to see a policeman coming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did it mean when you saw a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well - I don't know, it - I - we didn't ought to be afraid if we hadn't done anything wrong but - we - we were - brought up to be - to be afraid of a policeman, it's funny wa
sn't it. They'd say, a policeman'll have you, you see, they used to frighten us when we were children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who used to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 My parents and everybody. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you ever remember anything happening with a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 One day we were out - in a fi
eld next to - up - where we lived at Tidwell cottages, and we was chasing the cows around, catching hold of their tails and - making 'em run in the field, and a policeman was looking over a gate. Oh my goodness, weren't we afraid. He didn't do nothing to 
us you know but we were afraid as any - 'cos us - us thought us was going to go up prison.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there very much trouble in the area in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No, no, no, no, no. Nothing. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were the police local people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes. Yes. Broadhampston - used to live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Just one did the whole area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 One, yes, and then Ashburton. Used to come in Buckfastleigh, used to come out. Used to meet out there, had their meets out here you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you think he was all right with the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, he used to be all right with them. Specially when he'd go in a farm and have a - a drop of cider.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So they had a reputation but they were all right really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. All right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, no. Free. Free with the work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The farmer would be the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, he would, no he never used to come up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would he do any repairs or anything to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh if they - if they wanted repairs he - he'd have to have that done
 of course, but otherwise - then he did - it isn't very often he'd come up, he'd send the men up to do it themselves you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were there any occasions when you'd get invited down to the farmhouse or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, never. Never. Oh we were - we were - were down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was it a very big farm your father worked on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Big farm - oh you - it's that farm down - yes, Tidwell, that's right, that's the one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you ever remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, many times. Many times. I've seen mother cry before now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well I - 'course I couldn't have much to say 'cos I wasn't old enough. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But you say you tried very hard to help wherever possible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I know I did, I know I did, but - sometimes they wouldn't tell us you see what - what their - what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say your father had pneumonia that time, was that a rare occurrence, or was he ill very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, that was the first time he'd ever been ill. First time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I was living with Doctor Mole then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he come at all while he was ill?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Only to see him. Only to see him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did your mother cope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well she coped best way she could I suppose, oh Mr - Mr Downey - Smith used to come down and help her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
The minister. The Vicar, the Vicar, the Vicar. He used to come in and help her a lot. I don't know what she would have done without him. Well we - we never had father - he - if he - if he hadn't have turned up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember whether she ever got help - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213147\charrsid1131893 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 rom the Guardians or the Parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was he ever out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, weren't no chance to be out of work in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there anyone in the district whom the people strongly disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 There was nobody made to leave the village at any point?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you can't remember anything like rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Or anything like effigies being made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You didn't do any part time - jobs until you left school, when you went to Ashburton to do a full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What hours did you work when you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 On Ashburton? Oh I didn't used to get up 'til eight they used to call me at eight. And - they used to let me go to bed at quarter to nine.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 At night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you be working most of the time between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - we - in the kitchen I mean - in the house generally. Bedrooms and all of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have much time off for food, to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, well I used to have my food with them. Same as they had. In the dining room. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many people were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Two - Only he and her. The children -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 There weren't any sons or daughters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, they didn't have any children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have a title for this job, was it just general help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 General help, I - well she used to tell me what to do. See, 'cos I wasn't old enough to know what to do then I mean, in a house like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have all your meals in the dining room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where would you sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh I was right up in the attic. Three flight of stairs I had to go up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was the attic very big?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, it was great big place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You had the whole place to yourself did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes I did. I did. But the - it used to look out on the street so I used to look out there lots of me time. When I was upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But you wouldn't go upstairs until you'd finished your work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no. No. No. Only when I used to have to change for afternoon, change frock in the morning - for afternoon frock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there a servants hall or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Nothing, no. No, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about the second place, what was the relationship there, that was a bigger place wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, big place, it was a big place. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you eat with Mrs Bartlett there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, we had - we had our - we had our meals in the kitchen. And we had separate bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213147\charrsid1131893 Was thi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 s in the attic again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No. No that was rooms. That was real rooms. Up there. On Moorside I'm talking about now. That's what you mean don't you? That's right. Well we had - we had nice bedrooms up there. I used to sleep
 in a - in the old lady's part you see and the cook used to sleep in the other part, but the same kind of bedroom. Very nice bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 At the Ashburton job the mistress would supervise all the housework personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh everything - everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about Mrs Bartlett?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Her never had nothing to do with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who would organise that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The cook. The cook. She used to supervise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you be a parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213147\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 House parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213147\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 maid, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And a cook at Moorside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 U
sed to - the - the cook - well, yes I had to cook - cook it and then I used to have to take it in, serve it - serve the - Mr Bartlett used to carve and I used to serve all the vegetables, pour out the wine and p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8213147\charrsid1131893 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 ur out the water and - \{ILLEGIBLE\} pass it around. Pass the vegetables around.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So they would all eat together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They all eat together, they all eat together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But you didn't have anything to do with the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No, the cook done the cooking. Yes. All she had to do was dish it up and I had to take it in and - serve it. That's what I had to do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you had to look after everything really except for the cooking itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there a servants hall at all in Mrs Bartlett's place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, we didn't - we used to stay in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you feel at ease with the members of the family at Ashburton and Moorside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Ashburton was all right, 'twas more like home 'cos I was - I could talk to them like I could - but of course I 
had to - I had to ma'am and sir Mrs Bartlett, Mr Bartlett you see. They were - they was really gentry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What were they like as people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not very nice. Not very nice. She wasn't - 'twas he - 'twas her, 't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213147\charrsid1131893  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 wasn't him. In fact he - he went away from her t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213147\charrsid1131893 wo or three times. She was a de}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 mon. Oh had awful temper. Her say anything and - coo -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And in the second place at Moorside you had to address them as sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How would they address you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Edith. They - they never used your surname, not there. Some places they used their surnames. But they never used their surname, not there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you feel in the butchers shop that they were interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about the Bartlett's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh no, we never saw them. And - and they just - she used to come out and give the order for the meals in the morning, ten o'clock in the morning, I mean you never used to see them - after that. They used to be in their room or otherwise they'd go out you 
see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You wouldn't bump into them around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the mistress ever give any moral guidance to you servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they allow you any time to do just what you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We had afternoons off just like - ordinary places. From three to ten. - Up there. Three to ten up there. And - Sundays, every other Sunday.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many afternoons a week would you have off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 One afternoon. Thursday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that the same in Ashburton as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did Mrs Bartlett ever mind what you did when you went out or was it your own business
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Our own business, they never - they never interfered with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever feel homesick, you say you cried when you first left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I did in - in - in Orces but I - no, I was quite home up there. Well I knew - I knew the cook you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you had lots of companionship really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, yes. She helped me a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there anything you particularly disliked about the Bartlett house apart from the incident that provoked you leaving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. Nothing - nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Anything you liked, you liked the fact that you had your own bedroom?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I did, we did, yes, you see, yes. No, there was - there was nothing else - against them. Only when she had these tempers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did the housework go, did you find that very hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, it was easy. 'Cos I mean - I didn't have no scrubbing to do you see and not in those days, not up there I didn't, I did in Orces, but not up there. Orce's the butchers. That was the first place I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How do you spell that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Halse. Holse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That was the surname?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Surname, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was the washing sent out at the Bartlett's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No. Cook used to do it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who made or mended the family clothes at the Bartlett's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She used to have a - a - a lady - a woman come in and do all the mending and what was to be done. Woman come in purpose to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And the cook used to do all the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who was responsible for improvements or repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh they were. - You know, the Mr Bartlett was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 One daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How old was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well she was only about seven when I went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have a nanny for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No. No. She used to go to her school, used to go down to - the grammar school in Ashburton I used to have to take her down every morning. Fetch her every afternoon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time did she have to be at school by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Nine o'clock. And 
I used to have to go down - be down there by four o'clock to bring her home again. Help her dress and - do her hair sometimes - look after her in the main way I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did she ever do anything around the house herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She was Mr Bartlett's daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Daughter. Yes, she had to be waited on. Yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who put the children to bed, would you help put her to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I did sometimes. And sometimes the nurse, that was looking after the old lady, if we were busy, had extra cooking to do 
and I had to help the cook the old - the nurse used to put her to bed then that night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But the nurse would be more or less concerned with the old lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh the old lady, she had to do with the old lady all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the nurse live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. She lived in, she had a bedroom of her own next to the old lady's you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did you get on with the nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh she was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was she one of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Of a sort she was. She'd come in and have a cup of tea with us in the kitchen or anything, she didn't make no difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But did she regard herself as a servant the same as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no, she was a nurse, she didn't do nothing else you see. She was a real nurse. She kept to her work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What was the girls name, Miss Bea you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Miss Bea, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time did she have to go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there any age she put herself to bed or was there always somebody to help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I was left I expect by that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did she have a bedroom all to herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What were the sleeping arrangements of the whole family, Mrs Barlett had a room to herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. And Mr and Mrs Bartlett had a bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And the daughter had one as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that's right. And - the cook 
had one as well in - in that side you see. And I had one in - yes, the nurse had one and old Mrs - and Old lady's and - herself. We three was in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there a special room for bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes. A nice bathroom. We were - we had ours Saturday nights. We were allowed ours Saturday nights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You used the bathroom as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, same bathroom, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often did Miss be a have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Everyday had baths. Everyday, the night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often would they have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh - once a week. Saturdays I think they used to change. 'Twas - 'cos - the cook used to do the washing on Mondays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did the adults have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 In the dining room. Yes. Had to wait on them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where would Miss Bea have her meals when you were there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 With them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were there any exceptions, when they didn't have it in the dining room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They always had it in the dining room, yes. If they had any people in they - they had their meal in the dining room, bu
t I had to take the coffee in the drawing room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have many guests round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh they did have several. Several people come there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did Miss Bea have any other children come round for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, no, no, she never had anybody come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of cooking equipment was there in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 A - a - a stove, a range, a big range. Nothing else in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When would they have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 About eight o'clock. That was a cooked breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What members of the family would be present then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Mr and Mrs Bartlett. Then Miss Bea. Then I used to have to take her to school after that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time did you have to get up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 We was up at six o'clock every morning. Miss - the cook and I. Had to take tea up t
o them. Before they got up. Then they'd - they'd have their bath and then they'd come down and have their breakfast. Then they - sometimes they'd go out or - or just depends what they wanted to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they all have breakfast at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. The old lady used to have her meals with them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they have bacon and eggs and things for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. And scrambled eggs and - well everything in - what they - what they could afford in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did Mr Bartlett do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He - oh he did - he was - he had money, he lived -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He was sort of gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes. Never done no work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well we had - we didn't have a cooked - we had cooked evenings - a cooked meal evenings, 
dinner. Then - in the midday we - used - she used to make up a - a meal, well It was cooked meal but - spinach and - on toast or - some little thing like that you know. Egg - egg and - cheese, you know, little - tasty -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about Miss Bea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, she didn't come home to dinner. Be at school, that's right, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But all the other members would be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, all the others. Then of course she used to have a cooked meal with her mother and father when - when she came in the evening.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things would you have for the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh roast and - all kind - well, ordinary meals. Real - real meals in those days 'cos you could get the meat then couldn't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have your meals before or after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 After. Oh we had our meals after 'cos I had to serve at table you see, I couldn't have mine then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Then you'd have to clear it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right, clear it all out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long did dinner last in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Three quarters of an hour. Time they had all their courses, they have seven courses you know. Then they'd go in the drawing room then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Which part of the house was the dining room and drawing room in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Front. They both was in the front.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was it in Mr Bartlett}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213147\charrsid1131893 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 s side?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh what at the table. He - he was always head of the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What end of the house was it, was it in his section or her section?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh in Mr Bartlett's section. They had all that in - the old lady only just - go - used to go in her h
ouse and live. See, but she came into - their part for all her meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was anything like bread or jam or bottled fruit or pickles made in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well the - the cook used to make chutney and pickled onions. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about Mrs Bartlett?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, she - she never done nothing. No. Oh she never done a thing. She didn't know - I don't think she knew half what was done in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She never came round to inspect or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No. We never saw her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they go out very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They did, they went out a lot. Always out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would there be any occasions when they wouldn't be there for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no, they was always home to meals. But they always used to go out in the - in the morning and the afternoon somewhe
re, always out somewhere for - they used to be home to meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there any livestock kept for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, nothing like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about tinned or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Never - no, no, 'cos they used to have a gardener and he 
- he used to - a huge great garden, we had everything in that garden. Everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the gardener live out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, he - yes, he lived down in Ashburton. He lived there and he used to walk up there every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did he have his meals with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He went home to dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often a week would they have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh everyday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the children at Mrs Bartlett's ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, there's one daughter, one daughter there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did she have the same food as the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you servants have the same as the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where would the servants eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was Miss Bea allowed to talk at meals do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Could she choose what she wanted to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She had to have what was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say the Doctor had four children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would happen in that case?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well I - I had to have them in the kitchen and feed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 In the Doctor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How old were the children when you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh one was a baby. And the next was about two and four and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you always had them in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I always had the kitchen - well I had to look after them like a nurse girl really, bath them and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So what were you at the Doctor's, were you a parlourmaid or everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well I - I was anything, I had to do everything. Washing and - wait table and cooking and - look after the children, I had everything
 to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was it a much bigger house than Mrs Bartlett's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh yes, it was - two - six bedrooms upstairs and a bathroom. Dining room and drawing room and a big - quite big hall. And then of course there was the surgery you see. And a big waiting room. I had all that to keep clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many servants would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Only me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Just you on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have to do the cooking as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What hours did you have to work to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 'Til half past ten at night. Six o'clock in the morning. That was in olden days too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It sounds as if you'd need three or four people to do it doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well I had to do it. Look after the children as well, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you take them to nursery school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. They didn't go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have a governess?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 A - a governess came in after Ruth got about seven years old. Not before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long were you at the Doctor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 From 1917 to 1921?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have your own room at the Doctor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was it in the attic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, right up in the attic, but 'twas - 'twas nice bedroom. There was two up there. Nice bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they have lots of visitors all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh my goodness, lot of entertaining. Dinners at night you see, that's what it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have to wait on table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes. Used to have to bath the children, be cooking me dinner, putting dinner on ready to be cooked, bath the children, run up and down to see
 whether it's all right oh - mother - my mother - well mother - my mother was very angry. She was very angry about it - 'cos she said it was overworking me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did the Doctor call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Edith.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did you call him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have a big garden like at the Bartlett's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Well you can - you can se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7017036\charrsid1131893 e it. But it's up behind, but i}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 t's not - they're taking that away aren't they for a road. Part of that garden up the back. Yes, a lovely great garden up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you think they were self-sufficient in vegetables?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes. They used to have a gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many times a week do you think they'd eat meat at the Doctor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh every day. Every night, something different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, nothing like that, it was all fresh meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Or dried vegetables or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, nothing like that at all, all - grown foods and - fresh meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When you fed the children you'd be the only one there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes I was. I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you eat the same food as the doctor's family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes. Exactly the same. I used to wait until they'd finished theirs then I used to have mine see on my own because I had to feed the children, I couldn't - have my own and - and feed the children as well you see so I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would the children have theirs before or after the parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They had theirs when their - when their parents was having it. See I'd be feeding them and when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Be rushing in at the same time to serve the adults?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right, that's right. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time of day would breakfast be eaten at the Doctor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things would they have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Porridge and - fried bacon, they always started with porridge. Then they had fried bacon and then toast. Every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have to take the children along to school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No they didn't go to school, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were things like bread and jam made in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Make the jam, we made our own jam and bottled our own fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 In the Doctor's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes, yes. I used to do that in the afternoons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would the Doctor's wife ever help you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh my goodness. No. She never - she - yes, she - well she - she wa
s a nice - she was a nice person, I mean - I could get on with her different than I could Mrs Bartlett. I was sorry to leave there because I was so attached to the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were these children boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 John and - three girls and one boy. 
When John was a little baby - he wasn't more than three months old, they went up - he joined the Army then, he went up and - to - I don't know what the name of the place was, I had to take that baby. I went home then, and I had to take that baby and look 
after that baby three months old. Take it home with me, home to my mother's. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was that 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What happened to the rest of the family, who would be living there, the Doctor, his wife and the four children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, only 
- only myself and another doctor came in, Doctor Aronside, it - it's out like there now, she came in. But of course she wouldn't have nothing to do with that with me and the children you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you brought them home, just the one or all four of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
I bought 'em one. I don't - I forget - I can't - I don't know what happened to the other three. I believe they - I went to - believe they went with their grandmother. 'Cos Mrs Morrow went away as well you see. I think she went and stayed with her mo
ther, took the three oldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long did this last for, for four years while he was in the Army?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no. Until he went abroad - until he went overseas. For about - twelve months perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So how long were you actually living in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 As - I was there for four years in - living in the house altogether. Yes, four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When did you come home with John when he was three months old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh, he was just a baby you see. Just a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time would this be, would this be near the beginning when you moved in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And then you'd go back again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right. That's right. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who would look after the house while you were over here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I had to go out there every so ofte
n. Walk out there to see it was all right. They had a poor dog called Gip and - they thought they was going to leave him out with a friend in Buckfastleigh. But not likely, he - he followed me home, he was home - home outside the door the next morning. He
 wouldn't stay at Buckfastleigh. So I had to keep him as well then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 This was over in Tidwell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, at Tidwell cottages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The four children would be too young to help around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, of course they were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there a nanny or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. I was everything. Everything. Hardly believe it can you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You were working from six 'til half past ten at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. And if I wasn't up by six o'clock in the morning to have the children up, bell would ring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How much time during the day would you be with the children, would they spend much time with their parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They - in the - in the afternoon sometimes Mrs Morrow would have them. 'Course Doctor could never have 'em, he was too busy you se
e. Mrs Morrow would have 'em and - and play with 'em in the dining room - before they went to bed perhaps sometimes. While I was having me tea or - perhaps seeing to the dinner or something like that you see. She'd have 'em I - the dining room then. But I
 had to put them to bed, I had to bath 'em and put them to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you'd see more of them during the day really than their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I was more of a mother to 'em than what her was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did they call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Edith. Edith. They called me -
 they started to call me Edith. I used to travel about with 'em, Mrs Morrow, she used to take me everywhere she went. And I was always - I know once I went up to some place with her and she said, don't - you - you're - you're a nurse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7017036\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 girl, you aren't - you aren't a serv}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7017036\charrsid1131893 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 nt, you - you're a nurse - girl. Didn't want 'em to know that you see. I had the nurses clothes, you know, nurses uniform. I felt a proper fool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you usually wear that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Only just - only just that - whilst I was away you see
. She didn't want to be let down I suppose because - they had two nurses up there 'cos - 'twas a posh place that was, I didn't like it there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was the washing sent out at the Doctor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. Had to do it all. I mean, we used to - you know, the old coppers then in those times and a mangle to turn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who lived there then, the four children and the Doctor and his wife, anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Only they - unless they had visitors, there was always a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did all the children have separate rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No - yes, six rooms, well - they didn't - two - the girls used to sleep in one bedroom, and the boy - well John was only a baby you see, well - he used to be in a cot next to 'em. But after - after a little while I had John, when he got a bit older
 I had John in with me you see upstairs. To look after him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who looked after the responsibility of repairs and improvements to the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh Doctor Morrow. He had all that done himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time would the children go to bed at the Doctor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You'd put them all to bed at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, all the - well, you know, one after the other, I - used to put two in a - two in the bath at a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They had a bath every night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Every night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they have clean clothes to put on every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not every - not clean clothes every night but - used to be bathed or - well if their clothes was dirty we used to change them, say that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What cooking equipment did you use, was it a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, a range, yes. It's still there - I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time would the midday meal be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh just depends what time Doctor got in. Some - some - well you know what Doctors is, they never know when they're come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So there wasn't a regular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, not a regular meal in the middle of the day. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things would they eat midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh just - make up - perhaps a scrambled egg or - or - if it was in the summer we'd cheese and - tomatoes or - make up, you know, just like that, just a cold meal. That's allowe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893  had in the middle of the day and then we had a cooked meal in the night you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of meal would you have at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh first we'd have roast - meat or - some kind of meat done up and potatoes and vegetables and t
hen - a pudding and - coffee, cheese and coffee. Didn't have a seven course meal every - every night - every day when we was on our own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would anything special happen on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, no, just the - we had a - we had a midday - cooked meal Sunda
ys. Always a midday cooked meal Sundays 'cos I used to - go out you see in the afternoon. Once a fortnight, I generally went out once a fortnight, I - but the other afternoon I used to go out in the - go up to the chapel and then come home again and get t
he tea. I - I wasn't free, I mean, I couldn't go home or nothing of a - of a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many half days did you get off with the Doctor then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 One half a day a week. And then every day when it was my day out she'd - she'd go out to town and she wo
uldn't comeback to late and - I used to get so angry. Nearly four o'clock she would keep me waiting for her, 'cos I had to look after the children you see before she came back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Why did she do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well I - I - I don't think she liked - I don't 
think she really liked me having the time off. Yes. I don't, I don't think she really liked me having the time off. Because you see she had - she had the children, she was tired of the children then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It sounds in those days that women who had lots of children didn't look after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Didn't - they didn't - no, no. Well they never worried about 'em, I mean to say - I - well I - I was more of a mother to 'em as I said than - than their own mother was. And they used to love me and I used to love the 
children. I used to love the children. And Ruth, well - she was ever such a nice girl, Ruth was. I called my eldest daughter after her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you ever see anything of them now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. Oh well - Mrs Morrow's dead I know, 'cos Ruth wrote and told me
 and she - she - oh she wrote me such a lovely letter. She said how her mother used to tell about me you see and what I used to do. 'T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 was interesting that letter was, I've lost it now, I'm ever so vexed. 'Cos it was a lovely letter. And - her father was s
till living then but I expect he's passed on now. That was in Bath they lived. Yes. Bath was her home you see. Really, her was married away from Bath. And he was married from Bristol. He come from Bristol.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have any livestock at the Doctor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No, we didn't have anything like that. No. I didn't want nothing else to do I tell 'ee,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 All the time that you were there the children were put to bed by you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They didn't put themselves to bed at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, they weren't old enough. Weren't old enough. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there a servants hall or anywhere you could sit when you weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did Mrs Morrow supervise all the work personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, she never supervised the work but she - she would come out a
nd tell me about the meals. But she never - she - she'd come and - give me the list of the meals for the day and - now I should just have to carry on then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you feel you got on O.K. with the Morrow's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you like it there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, I did, I did, I - I really liked it there. I expect it was the children 'cos I was always very fond of children you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you feel the Doctor and his wife were interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did Mrs Morrow give any moral guidance to you do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I didn't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You weren't allowed much time to do just what you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I wasn't. Hadn't got time for anything. Not for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you not have any time off during the day at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You'd be on your feet all that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
All - all - unless it was my half day, and Sunday. I - I never - I never sat down at all. Never. Like - well, I - when I used to have to clean the silver I sat down to do it then but - but I mean tha
t was working. But I know I - I was on my legs all the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you feel homesick when you were at the Morrow's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It was like a home really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes, it was home that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have anyone else around you cold talk to when you were at the Morrow's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No. No. Well sometimes the servants may come out from Hillside and I'd look out - I look out the kitchen window and talk to them sometimes as they went down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many servants did they have up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Two. Two servants, and a gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was there anything you particularly liked or disliked about this situation at the Morrow's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I enjoyed it there. Enjoyed it there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 At both houses what was said if anything was left uneaten on the plate by the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh well they didn't say nothing, we - we took it away. They wouldn't - wouldn't make them eat it if they didn't want it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 This is true of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 If something was out of reach on the table did the children have to ask someone to pass it to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh yes, yes, they always had to ask. And mind their manners too. Yes, they was very strict about that. And they had to say their grace before meals. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you say grace with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They could if they wanted it, but - very rarely they did. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were they expected to hold their knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well they used to use a spoon and fork - before they was old enough to - use a knife you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would Miss Bea do that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that was - that was the same - well before she got old enough to use a knife an fork.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Could they bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No, they could - they 
had - well, they always had a nursery you see. They used to call it a nursery where they used to put all their playthings and that. They'd go up there you see, yes, and I'd go up there and - if I had spare time for - perhaps half an hour with them you kno
w afternoon. But that's the only time I had spare you see then 'cos I was busy all the what - after that prepared the meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Could they leave the table whenever they felt like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, they had to ask could leave the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was Mrs Morrow an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you mean Mrs Morrow herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 From the children's point of view?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes. But they were very strict. Very strict on the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 In what way were they strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well - if - if they didn't do anything righ
t they were punished. Sometimes we used to feel sorry for them 'cos they used - they used - he used to give 'em the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Even when they were that young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Perhaps he didn't hurt 'em very much but they always had to have it on their hand
. Give him - her hand. They were very - they were brought up very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things would they have to do wrong to get that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well perhaps they'd answer their parents or perhaps they - they wouldn't do what they wanted to do, you k
now, if - if they were told not to do a thing and they went and did it, they'd get it then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did the parents expect the children to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh well, they - they had to behave theirself in a proper manner. Answer them in a proper manner and do what they were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Was there any difference with the Bartlett's who only had one child, you hear that only children are more spoilt, do you think that was true?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh - Miss Bea was spoiled a little bit. But - the Morrow's weren't.
 Oh no. They were made known and - to know as soon as they could toddle. 'Cos you know they get - sometimes they get tempers at that age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How were the Morrow's supposed to behave towards their own brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well they used to fall out sometimes. But - if they have to be made - you know, they had to make it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 There wouldn't be much difference between their ages would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, no, no, there wasn't, there wasn't much difference you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of people did the parents hope that the children would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh I don't know, I - don't know anything about that. I don't know if - I never heard anything about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they ever give them instruction in anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They didn't have any lessons before they were old enough to have a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well - I used - I used to - go up in the nursery when - if I had time in the afternoons and I used to read them and tell them stories and - and - let 'em do little figures and things like I did, just - just little things like that, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would the parents thing, about the children swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Never done it, they never heard such thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would Mrs Morrow or Mrs Bartlett ever punish the children in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Well Miss - 
I don't know about Mrs Bartlett, she didn't - she didn't - Mr Bartlett - her - her father used to deal with her, but Mrs - Mrs Morrow and Mr Morrow used to correct the children, both of them. They both was in the same mind with them. One didn't - vindicat
e 'em and the other one - give 'em the hiding, no. They were both - brought up in the right way the Morrows were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 s birthdays any different from other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, they used to little parties. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Can you remember any particular one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, not any particular one, they was always - all served the same. I used to have to bake 'em a little cake and - they used to have a few friends in. In the afternoon, to tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did the friends come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well just - Buckfa
stleigh, yes. Different people that - had children. Doctor Williams' and - oh you don't know but he was other side. People like that they were friendly with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, used to bring little presents. Books mostly. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well, little story books what they could read you know. 'Course I always had to read them to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were there many books in the Morrows house and the Bartlett}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 s house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Mr Bartlett had a lot. He had a lot, he had a caseful. But Mr - Mr Morrow didn't have very many, only medical books, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He would get medical magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, that's right, things like that. They hadn't got much time for reading, he hadn't got much time for reading. 'Cos he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did they have in doctor's waiting rooms for people to read while they were waiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh just - you know - like they usually do now, books. Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you remember Doctor and Mrs Morrow reading very much? Apart from the Doctor reading his magazines?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I've never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893 - I don't think I've ever seen th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 em reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about Mrs Bartlett?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, well they - I never seen them reading either, no. 'Cos I wasn't allowed in there you see unless it's mealtimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have any musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes, they had a piano - a piano player, you know, what plays itself. Have you seen 'em. Is it - it's a - it's a piano, you can play it as a piano or you - or you can put a roll in and it plays. Yes, she - they had one of those. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was this the Morrows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Morrow - at the - the - Bartletts. Bartletts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the Morrows have any musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They had a piano. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Who played that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well nobody played it, not - not whilst I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It wasn't like a pianola?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, it was a - a grand piano. Goes right back over the door you know. Just - as it was. Well if anybody come in I mean and - if they had a - a do in the evening perhaps or - they'd have a sing-song you know 'cos they us
ed to entertain a lot, then - then - then they'd use the piano - for singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would the people who came round for evenings have meals with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, dinner, I had to cook - a dinner. Seven course or eight course dinner sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often would it be, once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh - oh, not once a week but - very often. Can't say exactly how many - how - how often but - they were always entertaining.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That would be at night time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 At night, eight o'clock. Doctor used to reckon to finis
h his surgery by eight you see. Six to seven he used to - and then he'd be free unless he was called out again you see. Very often he was called out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was this a normal thing to have dinner at eight o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, we kept that time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But the children would have theirs before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh they'm off to bed and a sleep by the time they have their dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they have the same dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. I used to give them force, I don't know if you know what that is, it's like a -
 it's a - like a - a cereal. Force every night they had with hot milk before they went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So their main meal would be in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, right in the middle of the day, I had to give - had to give them midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you take the children out shopping very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, not shopping but I used to take them for a walk sometimes in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Just walk around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were you allowed to talk to people while you were out with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not if I was - not if I was caught. - Didn't know everything when I went out for walk my dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But they wouldn't like you to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no, they didn't, I - they wouldn't allow me to go where there was - and I never had to go in Buckfastleigh. I - I used to go dow
n Colston Road, do you know Colston Road? I used to go down there and I used to go on the Ashburton Road sometimes. I had to go out of the town with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well 'cos I shouldn't - I shouldn't tell business I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They were that worried were they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I weren't worried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say you took Mrs Morrow's John back here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes. Yes. As a baby. Well - well my mother was over feeding the pigs, it was - and - she was this - this coming down the road, she didn't know what it 't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
was. Because I had the - I had John in the pram you see and - and the dog was coming along beside of me, and - and she never thought 'twas me coming down, coming - it was dark, you see, nearly dark you see. When I come down she was surprised 'cos I did
n't - I didn't know I was coming home. I couldn't let her know you see. I just walked home, so that's what I used to happen to my mother. She never knew when I was coming home. With the - with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you write very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I didn't write. I didn't write 'cos I mean I used to come once a week you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was this the only time you did bring children home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh if they go - if they went away I always had the children home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 All four of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. If - if - if th
ey went away, and one time - they was away like that, and mother used to come out and sleep with me out to Buckfastleigh then. For her to be in the house with me you see. That was a walk for her too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often would they go away, would they go away for holidays and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh yes, well when they went away for a holiday sometimes they took me with 'em, for their holiday. I - I mean I've been - I have been a lot of places with 'em for their holiday. Wigbury and - oh - lot of places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of places would they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well down Wigbury they used to hire a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893 chantey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 , well it's like a bungalow. Wigbury's down near Kingsbridge way. And - a lot of places - well, up her mother's you see, or we used to go up her mother's a lot in Bath an
d - there I was in the bedroom with the children there. I had the two children - two children was in a bedroom by theirself and I had two with me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you travelled around quite a bit with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh I travelled, yes, I used to love that. B
ut I - I was in a carriage by myself you know. Oh - oh you went - we went by train but I - I - I wasn't allowed - I was in a first class carriage and she was in a first class carriage you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where were the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They were with me. I had -
 I had those, oh I had the children. My goodness, yes. She used to come back in and out to see if I was all right. A great responsibility you know. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they ever go out for weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, never went for weekends. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they ever go out to other peoples houses for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you stay behind then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh I'd stay home then and look after the children. And look myself in then. Because in those days there was a lot of tramps and they used to come up there to sleep. And I used to be nervous you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often would they go out, about the same number of times as they entertained themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh - well - I can't hardly say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I suppose they'd be restricted by the Doctor's surgery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 That's right, yes, he would in one way, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did your mother and father take to John?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh they used to love him. Love him. Dear little thing he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did he call her, I suppose he was too young to know really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I don't know what he called my mother. No, I don't know, I can't - he couldn't speak, he weren't old enough, he was only a baby. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The other three children were with their granny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the Morrow's seem much different on holiday from what they did at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, of course they did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were they more relaxed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
They were and - I mean to say, they did - they treated me then as a nurse you see. And I - of course I wasn't with them at all, the children we
ren't with 'em for meals or anything then you see. Oh yes, I was - I was a - I was cut off from them if you understand me - then. But I didn't mind that 'cos I enjoyed myself, I shouldn't see the world if I didn't go with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What would you do, would you have much spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh yes, I had more spare time 'cos I hadn't got no work to do you see. And I was - solely concerned with the children then. I used to love it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you'd be able to go out at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, I used to go out - I mea
n used to go out a lot with the children then, took me out. I didn't mind having no work to do, I didn't care then about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How many times a year would they go on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long would that be for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say it was either to Dilbury or Bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Dilbury or - or up the country, up the country I used to go. And Bath. Bath and - Leyton Buzzard we went. You don't know Leyton Buzzard. Yes. Oh we used to go to Willowshot, different places, Bristol. Oh yes, we - 
I travelled a lot with them. Trowbridge. Do you know these places? Yes. Yes, used to go all round there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever go on a holiday with the Bartletts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, never. They never went on holiday - they never went on no holidays. No never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they do much entertaining?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, they didn't, they didn't - they didn't do much entertaining, no. They used to have visitors come of their own people and stay but - never had no - no outsiders come in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 There wasn't the same kind of family atmosphere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, 't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
wasn't - 't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 wasn't a bit the same up there. 'T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 wasn't a bit the same. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So really it was quite like a holiday every time you went away for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh it 'twas a holiday. Oh yes, lovely. Didn't cost me nothing. Used to see the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the Morrows and the Bartletts think it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes. Or - yes, Mrs Bartlett, well they was very strict about that too. And - and so was Doctor Morrow and Mrs Morrow. They had - always had to keep the Sabbath. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the children go to church or Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Yes. Yes, yes. I used to have take 'em in Sunday afternoons when it was nice Sunday afternoon at Buckfastleigh, I used to go to - up St Luke's church, you know St Luke's church, well the
y used to have children's service of Sunday afternoons, and I used to go there with them, well that was all right for me, I didn't mind that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you ever go to church with the Morrow's themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, not on me own, I went to the Methodist yo
u see. They used to go Church of England. Sunday morning I used to have to get up if they went to early Communion I used to get up - or have to get up early then. And they were - when they used to go - of course sometimes Doctor Morrow was out, I mean he 
couldn't go but - they used to always like to go early Communion. And Mrs Morrow would go eleven o'clock you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you go to the Buckfastleigh chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I'd go - I - well when I come home here I go up here you see but - when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often did you get off to come down here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Once a fortnight. Yes. 'Cos one Sunday - I had to be in one Sunday afternoon or - or not in 'cos I used to take the children out, but I mean I was - I wasn't on me own see, it 't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 wasn't me own time off I was with the
m, and then I used to have to be back to get the tea. Well then after tea - she'd put them to bed Sunday night, so that I could go out you see. 'Cos there weren't the - I don't think they used to bath 'em Sunday nights, just give 'em a wash. And - then I 
used to go to my own chapel, up the town. Had to be in by nine o'clock. Yes, in they days. No ten o'clock and eleven o'clock then, nine o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What time did they go to bed, did they go to bed fairly early as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well I don't know, I used to 
be up and gone to bed at ten o'clock and - just after I was gone up, I don't - they weren't gone to bed then 'cos I used to - take in whisky and - what they used to - you know, hot water and whisky before I went to bed. But I don't know nothing about them
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say grace was said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Always - always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. I don't think they - no, they never had family prayers, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they ever have any interests in politics do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They did but I don't know what they voted or nothing. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You never really talked about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I never heard anything, they never - they never spoke about politics in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Is that the same with the Bartletts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they take part in any sports or go to the races, play cards or things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 There was nothing like that in those days. No, they - never - never nothing like that, they never went -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They wouldn't go to the Buckfastleigh course or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No, they didn't take an interest in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Nor the Bartletts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What about hunting or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, nothing like that. He hadn't got the time, he was a doctor you see. His work was - occupied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did Mrs Morrow or Mrs Bartlett go out on their own much after?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Well to do their shopping or anything like that. But that was all, I mean 'cos they didn't go anywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They did the shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They done all the shopping, they got all the shopping in. She used to come in and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893  every}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
morning about ten o'clock to ask me what I wanted you see. And then she'd go down the town and get it. And Mrs Morrow used to be the same and she - of course the cook up there used to - tell her what they wanted. Of course I di
dn't have nothing to do with it - any meals up there. Bartletts. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did Mrs Bartlett or Mrs Morrow have many interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Mrs Bartlett didn't but Mrs Morrow did. With the - the Women's - I don't quite recall - Women's Institute, 
there's another name they - they got. Mother's Union. Mother's Union, yes. She had a lot to do with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did she ever have hen parties, coffee mornings or things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no, nothing like that in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say they went out together quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh they did. They did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did Mrs Morrow or Mrs Bartlett ever do any work for charity or sit on committees and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I don't know about sitting on committees but they did give to charity I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of charities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Well, anything that - say the hospital or - for the blind or - things like that. 'Cos there wasn't nothing much else on in those days you see. But it's different now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say Mr Bartlett didn't have an occupation really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. He didn't want to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say they had quite a lot of friends coming round, especially the Morrows, would they ever have balls or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Just - just a dinner and then they used to - possibly have a game of cards - on anything like that after. That was all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have this business where they separate the women from the men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No, they all went in the drawing room together after the meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of people were these friends, mainly doctors as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, not necessary doctors, just - ordinary friends - they had. 'Twas gentry you know. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The Doctor would be gentry would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes. Or they thought they was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were Mrs Morrow and Mrs Bartlett the same class do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, not a bit. Like chalk and cheese. Mrs Bartlett was so nice and Mrs Bartlett was so ugly. Well she was, I mean you couldn't go from her, she was - she was terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you think they were from the same background as the Doctor and Mr Bartlett though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh Mr Bartlett was a dear gentleman. He was - he was kind and - and sympathetic. He was nice. He had a - he had a life to live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She was a bit rough on him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes. Terrible. Terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She was Jew, that's what 'tis, she's a Jew see. And she looked like a jolly Jew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did she do before she met him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I don't know. Actress I believe she was. I believed she was actress. I'm not sure. But I think so. She's jolly good actress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of thing did Mrs Morrow do before she met the Doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 She was a - a matron in an - in an hospital. In Bath I think. Oh they were - they were a happy couple they were. Very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the Morrows or the Bartletts treat some of their friends differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I can't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did they have a more lavish spread for some?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh now, we all - no, the meals was always the same. I don't mean to say the same - same - meat and that, but - they were served the same. Yes. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did the guests behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Very nice. Some of 'em. They was very nice, I didn't used to mind they because they'd give me a tip. See? Yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You'd serve the food at the table would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, properly like, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would they have silver servers and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Everything. Coo yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You didn't have any instances where you didn't get on with the guests or didn't like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I got on with the guests - the guests used to like me too.
 I was - oh I got on with they all right. Fact some of 'em asked me if I would go to live with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Behind Mrs Morrows back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, come in the kitchen, yes. Yes. Yes. 'Course I wouldn't do that. Yes. Lady -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you think the Morrows and the 
Bartletts were sort of content with their station in life, or do you thing they would liked to have been in a higher position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I think they were very happy. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The same with the Bartletts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Had you known people like the Bartletts and the Morrows beforehand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes - do you mean - did I know the Bartletts and the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you come into contact with people like that very often before you started in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No. No. 'Cos I - the butchers shop was the
 first place I went to see. No, I - I - that was the first time I ever had experience of being with anybody like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You say the Vicar was very good and used to come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever go up to the Vicarage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No. No. They used to look after people who were sick and - bring 'em you know, food and that. That was all, we never went up there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did you think of their way of living, the Morrows and the Bartletts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Very very nice. Very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did their manners and general behaviour seem different from people you'd known before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Not Mrs Morrow's but - Mrs Bartlett was, but she was only one I mean Mr Bartlett and the old lady was a dear thing. Got on with them but 'tis Mrs Bartlett up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You said there was the business with the money underneath the handkerchief, who was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh that was Mrs Bartlett.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The young Mrs Bartlett?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes, yes, her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I thought it was the old one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh no, no, no, not her, my dear - my word, if s
he'd have known that wouldn't she have been annoyed. Poor old Mrs Bartlett, she was a real Christian. Had prayers and everything every knight and morning. She was - she was a dear old soul. But 'was this one. Other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did the Bartletts have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well they had to go in with the old lady you see, night times and mornings. Every night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When you were doing all these jobs in service did you send any money home to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Always - always.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How much did you get a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I had ten shill}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893 ings a month up at Mrs Bartlett}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And what at the Morrows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And I think - I had the same with her for a little while. Then I had three shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You got your board and food though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, got me board 
and food. I used to send me money home you see for mother to get me clothes or - of course in those days they - couldn't afford to buy, she had to pay out every week, so much every week. So I used to send my money home and mother - used to pay it like tha
t.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would the Morrows or the Bartletts provide your clothes for working in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No fear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you'd have to get your own black uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Everything. Got everything, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You said you went on these holidays, would you be paid during those holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, I - I never had anything to pay then. Everything was paid then and I didn't - nothing - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You'd still get your ten shillings a month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh they paid me the same. Yes, they paid me the same. But I - I - I didn't have 
nothing to do, you see. But they used to give me my wages back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever have anything like Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Only Boxing Day, Christmas and Boxing Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you go home on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. But Christmas Day they used to - I use
d to have to cook a - meal, they used to have a - Doctor - Williams and his wife down and - boys - Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 They'd have a bigger spread than ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What kind of things would they have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Roast turkey and - pudding, oh my goodness me, I can't remember. Jolly good lot of rummage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you think when you got married you helped your mother at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. I did. I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Then you took that over full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You did that 'til quite recently didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Twenty-eight years I did that, 'til I retired sixty-five. Sixty. I had a lovely present too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What did you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
set. It's lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were you ever a member of any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Or any sort of organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you have to do an apprenticeship or any training for any of these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have preferred another kind of job do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you feel that there was any sort of division of interest between employers and workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well of course I - I was treated as a servant. I mean. Both places. We were treated as servants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 I don't suppose you'd know about the division between workers, some people say there was a great division be
tween trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, I don't know nothing about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Do you think full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well I don't know I'm sure about that. I don't think it changed me in any way. '
Cos I always liked me work you see. Both places, I - I like housework, I like doing that sort of work, I'd rather do that than - go in a shop or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You had experience of it anyway helping your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you see much of your brothers and sisters when you left to go into service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh I used to see them when I come home you see. Yes. That's only time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It would cut you off socially there wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you have many friends where you went to in Ashburton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No. Well, I - I had one friend at Buckfastleigh who lived - she lives down out at Plain now. The first - not at - not the first little plain by your place, the other one at - as you go over the bridge. Well
 there's a big house there by the river, the bridge isn't there? Well I used - my friend used to live in there. She's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How often would you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh she used to come up with me sometimes of a evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you were allowed friends to visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
Oh - but - on me hour. If they went out or anything well she'd - they'd say, well you can have your friend in just for a little while, for company. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 But otherwise you were preoccupied with the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Could you ever go out in the evenings for a walk or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No fear. No. Only my time - my - when I was off duty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would you ever take this friend of yours down at the bridge up to Tidwell?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, I - I - she used to go maybe of a Sunday. Yes. Walk home and - with me. Not always but sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you take any interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. Never thought anything about 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You never took part in any elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When you were working in the Morrows and the Bartletts if you went out you had to be in by nine o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long had you known your husband when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Two and a half years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well we - we met in Ashburton in the recreation grou
nd. We'd been out to Bovey and there was something doing in Ashburton and they come back Ashburton, and we went down to see it in - some fete or other, and my sister and I went down there to just to see it, and of course these boys was there and they - th
ey - they walked home with us. Or they didn't walk home with us, they walked up top of the hill. We wouldn't let 'em go any further 'cos we thought we would get into trouble you see, my father and me mother knew. So we didn't - that - that was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Were you at the Morrows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No, that was at - at - that was - yes, let me see, yes, that's right, Morrows, and - they went - they came up so far as street and we said, you ain't going no further. So they had to go back again. They had to push their bikes up
 over all they hills. So we didn't think anything more of it. Well my sister and I was up doing the school on the Saturday morning and there was a letter from him, asking me to meet him. In Ashburton. I didn't go. I didn't go in. So - I had another letter
 - asking me to come out there. So he come out there and that was the starting of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He came out to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 To my mother's, yes. 'T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1315105\charrsid1131893  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 was all right, yes, it was all right, they didn't say nothing I thought to myself, I shall get into it, but they didn't, it passed off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How did you manage to see him if you were living at the Morrows?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, well when - when it was my - Sunday was mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 You met him on a Sunday was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, 'twas - I was on holiday, we were on - I was on me holidays 
and - we were settled at the Bovey you see, I told you all that, and - we came back - to the recreation ground and then he - I said - I've told you all that too. Well, at - then - after that - he come to visit me out there but he - in the evenings, Buckfa
stleigh in the evenings. And - Sunday afternoons we would meet and he - and after we got to know each other of course, and then he'd come and go home with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 The Morrows didn't mind him coming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 No, they didn't mind. Not after a little while. 'Co
urse - 'twas a little while before I mean - we got acquainted to take each other home properly, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Where did he live at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Bovey. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 What night was it in Ashburton, was it Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Thursdays. Thursdays, he used to come in Thursday nights, my afternoon off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 It was quite a way for him wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Well there you see it must have been true love.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So if you were in Buckfastleigh that's about ten miles between you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 More than ten miles to Bovey. Yes, 'cos - 'tis six miles to Ashburton from - isn't it - from Buckfastleigh. Yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Was he still living at Bovey just before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He was - he was still at Bovey when we married. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you go to live in Bovey for a little while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 
No. No. We - we had a little - up - up at the top, a little cottage - in the angle right up at the top of Lanscove. We were up there fourteen years. Then when my mother got ill of course I had to look after her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 So you came back down to Tidwell?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you ever go up to his parents place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Used to cycle right there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 When would you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Sunday - Sundays, Sundays, yes. Not - only Sundays I could go there. And me afternoon off and I didn't go home I'd go out there you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 How long after you met him was it that you went up to his house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh a long time. Two or three months I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 His house would be similar to yours would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Not so big as ours. No. She had a
 little sitting room and a kitchen and - two bedrooms and a bedroom up in the attic. There. Nice little house mind but - it was just big enough for them you see. He was living on his own, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 He was an only child at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes. At home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 His father was a farm labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 And he used to go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Did you often go up to his house after that first visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Well not too often. No, I - I couldn't go you see. Holidays, when I had me holidays 
I went out there to stay. When I used to get me holidays once a year. If I didn't have to go with the Morrows, I used to go out there then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Would there be many occasions when you didn't have to go with the morrows, you had holidays on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8653130 ER  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 Oh yes, yes, I've had holidays on me own and that counted on me own you see then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16009454 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7353437\charrsid1131893 This was during the month?
\par 
